INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(91245, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You remain undominated. How impressive.', 66337), -- Prey: Consul Nebulor (Hard)
(88994, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a remarkable story!\n\nHow ironic that the tale of Sai\'alyo, the first of the Zur\'ashar, was lost to time. Your efforts bring us closer to understanding this vital piece of our history.\n\nPlease, accept this keepsake as a mark of my gratitude for your dedication.\n\nFor now, I will delve deeper into our archives, uncovering relics that still long for discovery.\n\nReturn when the whispers of the world guide you back to me.', 66337), -- The Cauldron of Echoes
(89268, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So be it. Your path is set. This relic\'s truth awaits you.', 66337), -- Lost Legends
(89507, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work.\n\nYou are quickly becoming a model acolyte for He Who Guides Harvests.', 66337), -- Abundant Offerings
(91933, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah! I see you are already well-versed in the art of barter and trade!', 66337), -- The Abundant Honor
(91979, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. I\'m sure that will make for some excellent kindling.', 66263), -- Chop It Down
(91972, 66, 1005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An uneventful watch is more rewarding than an empty conversation.\n\nThe Blood Knights appreciate your service.', 66263), -- Hold the Watch
(91974, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Anar\'anel belore! You love to hear it. This news is sure to warm a few hearts for our cause.', 66263), -- Sunfire to the Blade
(89276, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, this shall do very nicely.', 66263), -- Light Snacks
(91693, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Splendid.\n\nI dearly hope you find some time to enjoy yourself while court is in season. While I do appreciate the sullen, results-driven sort, you could stand to smile.', 66263), -- The Subtle Game
(91629, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will have my valet send for them at once.', 66263), -- High Esteem
(91628, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, so the rumors are true about your efficiency.\n\nExcellent. Now we can begin the game.', 66263), -- Honored Guests
(91627, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n. Welcome to my Haven--a sanctuary from the world\'s turmoil since the days of Anasterian.\n\nSome presume this to be merely a frivolous party, but on these beautiful gilded grounds, decisions have been made over wine that have shaped the fates of entire generations.', 66263), -- Saltheril's Haven
(94790, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More samples, excellent! The console hungers...', 66263), -- Research Console: Exploring the Void
(92662, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s one crisis averted, though this singularity\'s power was nothing compared to the one in the upper citadel. Our researchers are still working on a permanent solution, but at least we\'ve only one cosmic disaster to focus on now.\n\nA shame the tools didn\'t survive. Our researchers could have used them to improve our Singularity Anchor.', 66263), -- Core Collapse
(92661, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. He was dangerously adept at crafting void weaponry. The Devouring Host\'s blades will be a bit duller with him dead.\n\nUnfortunately, we have a much bigger problem.', 66263), -- Hammer Meet Anvil
(92660, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marvelous! Let\'s see what you\'ve got.\n\n<Lysikas stares blankly at the tools you\'ve acquired.>\n\nI have no idea how to use any of these.', 66263), -- Null Implements
(92659, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It should take them some time to get back to capacity. That\'ll keep the pressure off, at least for a while.', 66263), -- Resource Denial
(92658, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good! The less Void energy the domanaar have to throw at us the better. I\'ll make sure this gets back to the assault. It\'ll help keep the defenses running.', 66263), -- Tactical Acquisition
(91546, 1005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad I went through with this. Thanks for coming with me.\n\nLet\'s get back to the others in the Voidstorm, $n.', 66263), -- To Be Changed
(92512, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Leona\'s determination and willingness to fight for our people is admirable.\n\nShe fought hard and sacrificed much to reach this point, and her life will be forever marked by those trials. But the ren\'dorei are stronger for it.\n\nWho would\'ve thought that such a dark and predatory world would be the catalyst for a brighter future?', 66263), -- Devourer
(92511, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That voice. A domanaar. I think I can sense it now. He\'ll come for us if we don\'t find him first.', 66263), -- Event Horizon
(92510, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I believe we have some equipment that can be repurposed to help Leona return to us.', 66263), -- Dark Infusion
(92509, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is no question now, $n. Demon hunters are the apex predators on this planet.', 66263), -- One Cruel Implement
(92508, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, this captured void energy will do nicely.', 66263), -- The Mark of Sacrifice
(92507, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve only ever wanted to protect my people. Just like how demon hunters protect Azeroth.', 66263), -- A More Potent Foe
(92506, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, that looks like enough. We\'re nearly prepared, $n.', 66263), -- The Soul Price
(92505, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I haven\'t set foot on Argus in years. A dead world, populated by a broken people and their memories.', 66263), -- Truth of the Past
(93970, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you hear that? It most certainly did something! \n\nHuzzah!', 66263), -- Researching the Storm
(94469, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to you, the singularity anchor survived another assault. Take this as a sign of our appreciation.', 66263), -- A Handful of Voidlight Marl
(90860, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Shadowguard got what they deserved.\n\nBut I am not blameless, $n. Even now, shadows linger inside me.\n\nFor the safety of everyone, I should go.', 66263), -- Shedding the Yoke
(88708, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In all our time together, I never expected Matrean would fall prey to the Void. I failed him.\n\nBut I will not fail our people again.\n\nWe should take great care in the Voidstorm and stay only as long as we must.', 66263), -- Violent Conclusions
(87672, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kelia\'s brow furrows as she concentrates on the energy captured by the device.>\n\nThese readings are alarming. We should head back immediately.', 66263), -- Void is in the Air
(88653, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve bathed in their essence and glow with promise, hero.\n\nWe, too, have tasted their power. It courses through us. Strengthens us.', 66263), -- Yolks on You
(87391, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He ATE the samples?\n\nI\'m afraid the Void\'s grip on Matrean is growing firm.', 66263), -- Sampling the Local Fare
(87388, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There may be a time and place for caution, but now is not that time.\n\nI hunger for results!', 66263), -- A Bigger Beast
(88755, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Void peers back, but I shall not avert my gaze.', 66263), -- Scholarly Pursuits
(92948, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Forgive me, $p. That all happened so quickly.\n\nWas any of it even true? But what else could that spirit have been?\n\nAn entire world... civilizations that used to thrive right where we stand? Could that really be?\n\nI can tell you only one thing for certain. \n\nThis will haunt me for the rest of my days.', 66263), -- In Over My Head
(92946, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If this specter and his tablets are to be believed, this world was once thriving with multiple civilizations.\n\nJust like on Azeroth, they fought endless wars. They asked Akintunde for a weapon to end all wars, and he delivered... by making one that ended everything.', 66263), -- Buried in the Dark
(92944, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you hear that? This world was called Predacea!\n\nWhat a revelation!', 66263), -- Sifting Through Void
(92939, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Yes, you found more rubble!\n\nHave you noticed the runes carved on these rocks emanate Void? Creatures of Voidstorm seem to have an endless hunger for that magic.\n\nSo, I think these beasts are eating the Void in these runes. At least, that makes the most sense.', 66263), -- It's Not Just a Rock!
(91561, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the mutated pathogen dealt with and the antidote in hand, we should be safe from further outbreaks. Thank you for your assistance, $n.', 66263), -- Bloodborne Pathogen
(93801, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts and assistance are both noted and appreciated.', 66263), -- Calculated Culling
(91560, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Riftwalker Lorn is dead? This is troubling news. \n\nYou have my gratitude for saving as many of the ren\'dorei as you did.', 66263), -- Expunging Explorers
(91558, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Absolutely beautiful! I only hope these flowers can provide a clue to cure my brethren.', 66263), -- Pestilent Petals
(91559, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marvelous. Let us dissect these immediately, before they spoil.', 66263), -- Virulent Vermin
(90875, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stay. I must. Men of Void, cannot find brothers and sisters. Finish, must. Only I.\n\nYou, good. Friend. But. Trust, can\'t. Trust, only when brothers and sisters safe.\n\n<She then holds her staff forward, offering it to Juras. Though he seems reluctant to take it, Tul\'amar does not waver.>', 66263), -- Across Worlds
(91606, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Charonus is our enemy. I am unsurprised. He always scraped together power through whatever means necessary, even stooping so low as to bow and scrape to Xal\'atath. Disgraceful. \n\nNonetheless, let us hear their proposition.', 66263), -- Voidscar Arena: Clearing House
(91605, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We shall find glory in a battle yet.', 66263), -- Voidscar Arena: The Wrong Side
(91603, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will prevent further spread of the grafting. However, we must still deal with what remains ourselves. \n\nHow troublesome.', 66263), -- Voidscar Arena: Two Against One
(94855, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who dares stage forces here? Without announcing themselves?\n\nNoxian? Decimus? We will root them out and make them pay.', 66263), -- Voidscar Arena: Setting It Aside
(94849, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. The mortal was blinded by their pain, so they never would have listened to reason. \n\nAll they cared for anymore was the fight.', 66263), -- Voidscar Arena: A Familiar Grudge
(94848, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, Vidious is also under attack by shadowgrafted monsters? \n\nI see. \n\n<Ziadan almost smiles.> \n\nSo, he did not betray my expectations after all. Perhaps we keep him alive a little longer. \n\nBut there is a third. An interloper.', 66263), -- Voidscar Arena: Pre-Provoked Violence
(92159, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done with Havazza. I hated the idea that she\'d get away from this without any consequences.\n\nOn the positive side, I can learn a lot from this entity for future disturbances.', 66263), -- A Final Destination
(92158, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is tiny, harmless, and trapped.\n\nThere is one last thing to do.', 66263), -- Let It In
(92157, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m sorry. I let that go on far too long. My curiosity outweighed my common sense.', 66263), -- Ritual Activity
(92156, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s still hungry. The meals are never enough.\n\nThat\'s why I\'m so weakened. It was constantly nagging me. You seem strong enough, though.', 66263), -- It Follows Me
(92155, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I saw your flight through the air. And I heard the screaming.\n\n...How interesting.', 66263), -- Object Exorcism
(92390, 45, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lanlae shakes off the pain of the assault and forces a smile to her face.>\n\nHow thrilling! That was a proper good scare.', 66263), -- Risk for Research
(94844, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. My minions must grow stronger.', 66263), -- Voidscar Arena: For My Horde
(94845, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shadowgraft? Pathetic.\n\nOnly domanaar with less skill and intelligence use it. It empowers creatures--makes them blind with violent urges.\n\nBut the creatures lose all cunning. All interest. It is a single flavor, not the complex notes of heartache and betrayal. It is boring.', 66263), -- Voidscar Arena: The Bastion of Might
(91566, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You. You look ready for a battle.\n\nYour Horde is noble. You fight for honor. For glory. Sometimes, for the joy of it.\n\nYour eternal conflict with the Alliance is delicious. I shall savor it.', 66263), -- Voidscar Arena: The Hate Spire
(90874, 433, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<She counts out the portal runes in your possession and nods in approval.>\n\nYes. Good.', 66263), -- Their Violent Ends
(90873, 433, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tul\'amar tilts her head at the freed draenei hiding behind her.>\n\nI see. Good. You good.', 66263), -- These Violent Delights
(90872, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Now, more. Brothers and sisters, help.\n\nAnd men of Void, kill.', 66263), -- Drenched In It
(90866, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Blood! Is blood. Yes?\n\n<She looks to one of her kin, who assures her that she\'s got the right word this time.>\n\nGood. Now see.', 66263), -- Universal Language
(90858, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can feel Kifaan\'s hesitation every time our gaze meets. He is afraid of me...', 66263), -- Repress the Oppressors
(93396, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve been focusing on my own feelings so much that I never stopped to think about how Veraan might feel.\n\nI may not have fared any better had they pumped ME full of Void.', 66263), -- Bursting at the Seams
(90852, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. You helped me see my sister again. For that, I can never repay you.\n\nVeraan is changed. Angry. Tormented by despair. Let us tread delicately.', 66263), -- Techno-Magnetic Pulse
(90851, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Violence is rarely an occasion for celebration, but I am glad we have at least slowed the deeds occurring here.', 66263), -- Eating Their Own
(90848, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Veraan\'s essence may have been twisted by the Shadowguard, but the rebellion gives me hope.\n\nCan the dissidents be snatched from the Void\'s grip entirely?', 66263), -- She Started the Fire
(92890, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your assistance. Please accept these as thanks.', 66263), -- A Handful of Voidlight Marl
(92739, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Lightbloom is persistent, but so are you. Aln\'hara\'s lands and creatures remain thanks to your efforts.\n\nThe young are being restored to their natural habitat, freed of the spores--all of them except this one. It is too small for the wild.\n\nIt will need a caregiver, and I think it has bonded to you.', 66263), -- O.K. Bloomer
(92737, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a shame to destroy the creatures of Harandar, but sometimes it must be done to protect the land.', 66263), -- Light Carnage
(92738, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have saved so many. The balance of the land may still stand thanks to your efforts.', 66263), -- Potatoad Tots
(92736, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This herd was seized recently--the signs you discovered make that clear. This encroachment is pressing into untainted lands, and the herds could be depleted beyond recovery.\n\nI appreciate your help, but there is more that must be done.', 66263), -- Light Stroll
(92732, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<This corpse appears to be covered with Lightbloom spores and was fighting recently. It must be what the scout saw.>', 66263), -- Light Disturbance
(91381, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done, then.\n\nYou did well to survive untainted. The wilds are a dangerous place, and survival is never a guarantee.\n\nNow go. I must remain and ensure that these abominations cannot spread any further.', 66263), -- Reticent Evil
(91378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are quite the accomplished slayer of aberrations. Perhaps you should consider a vocation in monster-hunting.', 66263), -- You Are Legend
(91379, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve culled the worst of the growths to the north... but there are smaller ones already beginning to sprout. Where are they coming from?\n\nThere must be a source, and we\'ll have to find it if we mean to solve this thing.', 66263), -- Decayed Land
(91376, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Goddess forfend. This is not fungarian flesh at all.\n\nWhat ARE they?', 66263), -- Little Monsters
(91377, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is so much worse than I thought.\n\nWe have to find the source of this and destroy it before it infects something bigger and more dangerous than a fungarian.', 66263), -- Spawn of the Dead
(90834, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I owe you a great debt, $n. At least now I can protect my people as I learn the ways of the Shul\'ka.\n\nMy only regret is being separated from Chua.', 66263), -- From This Point Forward
(90833, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know it was stupid and I should be dead. I feel confused about surviving the ritual but no longer being able to hear the goddess. I\'m sorry, $n. I shouldn\'t have done that.\n\nAt least it\'s over. Now to apologize to Amarakk. He\'s probably done with me.', 66263), -- The Final Rite
(90832, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done. There is but one thing left to do once En\'liahn has recovered.\n\nBut first, we should leave the rift immediately. This is no place to linger.', 66263), -- As Her Voice Goes Silent
(90830, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now it is time to see if young En\'liahn will survive the ritual or be consumed by the rift.', 66263), -- The Path Will Reveal Itself
(90831, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well for one who is not Shul\'ka.\n\nUnfortunately, the Rift of Aln never rests. I think you\'ll be back.', 66263), -- Doing Is Becoming
(90829, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you came. Amarakk is my Shul\'ka mentor. He says your help is not strictly forbidden.\n\nI can use all I can get.', 66263), -- Meeting My Mentor
(90827, 273, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should be more than enough.\n\nI\'ll be careful with them. I wouldn\'t want to poison myself prematurely.', 66263), -- Only the Poisonous Parts
(90826, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.\n\n<En\'liahn looks like he\'s getting worse.>\n\nI hope the water is as powerful as my mentor says it is. The strong poison of these creatures suggests I\'m going to need it to survive the ritual.', 66263), -- The Healing Waters of Ahl'ua
(90824, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Chua sent you? He\'s not out here again is he?\n\nMind lending me a hand?', 66263), -- My Brother's Alive!
(92448, 1, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ohhh... this Dust sparkles like a dream!\n\nIf you find more, bring it to me! I\'ve treasures rare and wonderful to trade for in exchange!', 66263), -- Where Dust Dances
(90535, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There. Now you are part of Harandar.', 66263), -- Leave Your Mark
(90534, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can\'t say I\'ve ever seen a place like this before. But I like it. I can see how the haranir were drawn here. How Orweyna grew up here and learned all she learned.\n\nBah, look at me getting sentimental. What\'s next?', 66263), -- The Home of the Haranir
(90533, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m pleased that Monte came this way to visit. But I can see that he is as out of his depth here as I was in Undermine.', 66263), -- Go Get Orweyna!
(91553, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you so much for rescuing me... not that I needed it of course. Anyway, you seem to be pretty good yourself. So after talking with everyone, we all agreed to make you a part of our group! \n\nBe proud. This is an honor only few have received, but you\'ve earned every bit. You are officially one of us! Be proud, stand tall, and never give up!', 66263), -- Haranir Never Say Die!
(91552, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it? Great! That\'s really great!\n\nWith more of those petalwings gone, we can finally focus on helping Shao\'mal!', 66263), -- Feathered Fury
(91551, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great job! Those petalwings might think twice now before settling down in our pla--I mean hunting area!', 66263), -- De-nest-stration
(91550, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That monstrous petalwing took him! And we stood there... frozen like fungus! \n\n<Ilomai shakes her head and gathers her resolve.>\n\nWe don\'t have time to be scared. We move. Now.', 66263), -- A Game of Silence and Shadow
(90601, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you return! And with so many glowshrooms. Excellent. I hope you didn\'t have anything strange happen.\n\nThank you for collecting all of these. It will take me some time to reproduce Ru\'gar\'s methods, but I have hope now that we can continue his work.', 66263), -- Gathering Glowshrooms
(90602, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is this? Ru\'gar\'s notes on his cultivation efforts!\n\nThis is fantastic. I can try to reproduce his work now.\n\nGood work taking out Gomphusta, also. May this throw the fungarians into disarray and keep travelers on the roads safer.', 66263), -- Gomphusta
(90963, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This seems to be a safe location from which to plan our next moves, and one of the plants Ru\'gar mentioned to me grows in this area as well.', 66263), -- Caves of the Cleft
(90569, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found so many! Thank you.\n\nThese seeds were very important to Ru\'gar. I don\'t know much about gardening, but maybe I can give it a try.', 66263), -- Back in the Bag
(90540, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $n. I saw the freed rutaani rushing toward Har\'mara.\n\nThese fungarians were in pursuit, but I got the jump on them.', 66263), -- Rutaani Rescue
(90537, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Fungal Cleft, $n. The local fungarians here are more volatile than those at Har\'mara.\n\nThey have no concept of balance and strive to spread their spores far and wide, overcrowding the nearby rutaani of Blooming Terrace and threatening to spill out into the rest of Harandar.\n\nThe captured rutaani must be within the settlement.', 66263), -- Late Bloomers
(91876, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p, for your help. Because of you, I was able to keep up my routines even with those fires.\n\nPerhaps one day, we might see a sprout--even if it takes many years.\n\nAnd I shall be ever ready to resume my duties as Rootwarden, should hope bloom.', 66263), -- Tending Hope
(91874, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$p, the smell of smoke fills me with the same dread I felt on that terrible day.\n\nThere is much heat still trapped within the largest roots, and in the right circumstances, the burning begins anew.\n\nIf we have any hope of seeing the roots restored one day, we have to be vigilant against even small fires.\n\nAt best, they undo our work, but at worst, they could spread to consume what remains.\n\nThank you for helping me keep watch.', 66263), -- Flare Up
(91875, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will do nicely, for today. Just give me a moment to mix...\n\n$p, do you smell smoke?', 66263), -- Natural Remedy
(91873, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for helping to protect what may still live of Teldrassil.\n\nIt may be that nothing remains. Some of these roots still smolder.\n\nYet I vowed to serve as Rootwarden, and I will not fail a second time, if there is any hope. I choose each day to believe there may be--that Teldrassil could bloom again.\n\nThough I may only be preserving her memory.', 66263), -- Buffer Zone
(91872, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I lived far longer before I became Rootwarden than after.\n\nYet Teldrassil will always be what defines my life.', 66263), -- The Former Rootwarden
(91589, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done more than fill bowls--you have upheld something fragile and vital. For the peace of Har\'mara, we thank you.', 66263), -- Root Dash Delivery
(91588, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All is ready. Let those who share in this meal remember that unity is not ease--it is effort.', 66263), -- Harandar's Kitchen
(91587, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This carcass breathes new sustenance into the fungarians and the peace we uphold.', 66263), -- Carcass Cuisine
(91586, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. The rutaani will accept this without complaint. Peace rests on gestures such as these.', 66263), -- Soil-Based Alternatives
(91585, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Even an old cook can work wonders with good hands beside him.', 66263), -- Fresh from the Garden
(92531, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat is quite de ghost story!\n\nI am sad dat I will not talk to Sij\'ta again, and dat Kulzi has lost his loa speaker, but I am glad Sij\'ta has found peace at last.\n\nI will go and speak to Kulzi. I hope there are no hard feelings there.', 66263), -- The Medicine Loa's Shrine
(87317, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is dis nonsense? The loa speaker gets to move on?\n\nDis is all his fault!', 66263), -- Denial Denied
(87268, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wish I knew why I broke de staff.\n\nI think it\'s time for de warlord to face his memories, just like we are.\n\nOtherwise, we gonna be trapped in dis curse forever. We gotta remember, even if we don\'t want to.', 66263), -- Required Repentance
(87267, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is dis ya bring me?\n\nA broken staff?', 66263), -- Demands Unmet
(87256, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With dis many, we can work our magic to heal de whole war party too!', 66263), -- Alternative Medicine
(87254, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bah! Dat loa...\n\n<Loa Speaker Sij\'ta spits on the ground.>\n\nEven the forbidden ritual fails to heal Akutu? What curse is this?', 66263), -- Curse Cleanse
(93437, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, hash\'ura. Truly.\n\nThe battle against de echoes will continue. However, it would seem dey cannot return after being slain now dat their leader has been dealt with.\n\nMemories stirred my blood these last few days. Now we can all rest. Perhaps even move on?\n\nBah! It\'s just de ravin\' of an old warrior. Do not mind me. \n\nSimply consider myself in your debt.', 66263), -- In Their Own Blood
(93436, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De echoes are runnin\' from de battlefield like scared hogs because of your work!', 66263), -- Hex the Innocent, Disrupt the Guilty
(93435, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I admit it, $n: knowin\' you have slain de instigators brings warmth to my old bones.\n\nDoes dat lower your opinion of me?', 66263), -- Four Instigators
(93432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See? An endless ocean.\n\nPerhaps Doru will learn something from de ashes.', 66263), -- Swords to Plowshares
(93433, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Barriers holdin\'? Good.\n\nNow we can focus on de offensive.', 66263), -- Shrine, Sealed, Delivered
(93440, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zul\'jarra sent you, hash\'ura?\n\nHeh. She must be tired of waitin\' on us to make headway.', 66263), -- Personal History
(91400, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for collecting dem. Now our foes won\'t get de advantage of fine Amani crafting.', 66263), -- Blades of the Fallen
(91401, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I got a plan for de bones. Thanks.', 66263), -- Dead by Dusk
(91398, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank ya. Dese are going straight into de fire.', 66263), -- Tomes of Terror
(91402, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Never seen one of dem before and hope I don\'t see dem again. Nicely done.', 66263), -- Ultra Deadly Ultradon
(91399, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our hunters gonna make good use of de powder. Thank ya.', 66263), -- Ashes of the Void
(91556, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope it brings his spirit peace. And mine.', 66263), -- Loa's Flame
(91070, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. That\'s all of it.', 66263), -- Reclaim the Goods
(91071, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I saw de small ones run away in terror. Well done, $c.', 66263), -- The Menace of Atal'Abasi
(91069, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you hear dat?\n\nIt\'s quiet.\n\nDat is de sound of vengeance.', 66263), -- Vengeance for Tolbani
(94867, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vakala sent you? She was right to think dis place was dangerous.', 66263), -- Lost in Atal'Abasi
(92167, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The leader was a kobyss? What is a kobyss?!\n\nI mean... well done, hero! You have served your loa well!\n\nNow that these murlocs are safe, it is time for us to be going!', 66263), -- There Can Be Only One
(92166, 17, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found her! Thank you! Erm, I mean... the Loa of Murlocs grants you favor, champion.', 66263), -- Following Suit
(92165, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Witness the power of my champion! Be fed, my people, and hunger no more!', 66263), -- Fish Are Food, Not Friends
(92164, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you finished?\n\n<King Mrgl-Mrgl clears his throat when he sees one of his \"followers\" eyeing him suspiciously.>\n\nI mean, it is finished. The Deepfin shall trouble us no more!', 66263), -- Murloc Madness
(93049, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All in perfect condition!\n\nMaybe you should be de apprentice instead.', 66263), -- Homework Support
(93048, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat boy still needs a lot of practice, but you helped him get out of his head and just feel de rhythm.', 66263), -- Got No Rhythm
(92386, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your assistance. Please accept these as thanks.', 66263), -- A Handful of Voidlight Marl
(93051, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You fought well.\n\nYour own strength proved Dar\'rak can hold his own against warriors far stronger than himself.\n\nI never expected him to beat you, $n. But de fact that he still breathes is an impressive enough feat, hm?', 66263), -- The Final Exam
(89233, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank ya for helpin\' me. Kagara, Zak\'kash... I hope we can all still be friends after dis.\n\n<Namaji furrows her brow but then smiles.>\n\nI best go tell my festival partner of my decision den! Thank you again.', 66263), -- Love Triangle
(89231, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'A lovely headdress! From Zak\'kash? He is so thoughtful!\n\nI\'d be happy to go to de festival wit\' him. I\'ll finish my work here first and then go tell him myself.\n\nThank you for deliverin\' dis!', 66263), -- A Fighter Not a Lover
(89230, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Dis is from Kagara? I\'ve always wanted one of these!\n\nI\'d be happy to go to de festival wit\' him. I\'ll finish my work here first and den go tell him myself.\n\nThank you for deliverin\' dis!', 66263), -- A Lover Not a Fighter
(92453, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, $n! I jumped off de waterfall and I killed a big lizard!\n\nI know you helped.\n\nJynx helped too.\n\nThanks!', 66263), -- Fearless
(92452, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wasn\'t sure how much longer I\'d last out here. I was runnin\' out of rocks!', 66263), -- Not According to Plan
(92451, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ani\'s bag of treasured trinkets sits empty on the marsh bank, already sinking into the soft mud.>', 66263), -- I Think I Can
(92450, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See? It\'s a long way down.', 66263), -- Growing Up is Hard
(89560, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for helpin\' us on dis journey, $p.\n\nI didn\'t think Iz\'ken would come, and he didn\'t think he\'d be welcome.\n\nI think Iz\'ken and I realize now... de worst trick our mother pulled was pittin\' us against each other.', 66263), -- A Quiet Farewell
(89559, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The others in de tribe still revere mother and mourn her death.\n\nBut since she died, I\'ve mostly just been missin\' Iz\'ken.\n\nShe drove my brother away.\n\nBut... her death has brought him back. At least for dis ritual.', 66263), -- Reasonless Worship
(89513, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kan\'sha\'s been a long-time friend, and I spend many of my nights restin\' here under her pines when I can\'t go home.\n\nOur tribe warns folks to be watchin\' for her falling branches, but dey never hit me. Not one scar or bruise came from her.', 66263), -- Kindling Aplenty
(93047, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are an impressive hunter, dat is for sure. Thank you for helpin\' us out here.', 66263), -- Butchery Basics
(89506, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At first when Iz\'ken left us, I thought mother didn\'t care. Even at her deathbed she never once mentioned him.\n\nBut she felt guilty when he left. Her tantrums toward me carried de shame, I think.\n\nI wish she could have admitted it, but I knew that would neva\' happen.\n\nOur tribe sees mother as unstoppable... fearless.\n\nBut sometimes it\'s what\'s inside dat\'s hardest to face.', 66263), -- Strong Ties
(89503, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I asked for you help without tellin\' you about how my mother treated my brother and me. I don\'t speak much about my family. I learned not to.\n\nI still don\'t understand why she was the way she was. Maybe somethin\' happened to her. Somethin\' that\'d cause all dat pain... Maybe pain and chaos were all she knew herself.\n\nBut in de tribe, she inspired many--at least she can remain a mother to dem.', 66263), -- Somber Siblings
(91750, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It was a Twilight\'s Blade monster!\n\nI hope Furgh and the others will be okay now that it is dead.', 66263), -- Perils of Trust
(93734, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You didn\'t need to burn my things...', 66263), -- Precious Trinkets
(91749, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Furgh licks his chops. They are wet with drool.>\n\nThe bag feels... tempting. I don\'t like it!\n\nGood he kept this away from others, but also very bad for him.', 66263), -- It's Just Not Right
(93261, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So de Twilight\'s Blade hasn\'t just hurt de Revantusk, but our wildlife as well? We must keep an eye on de cultists and protect Nalorakk\'s Prowl from their pollution!\n\nDe health of our people and our crabs is my top priority. Seeing my people starve under my watch filled me with rage, and guilt... like I was tarnishing my mother\'s memory as head river-walker.\n\nYour aid has helped me become de leader my river-walkers need.\n\nThank you, $n. You\'re forever welcome with de Revantusk.', 66263), -- A Crab of Unusual Size
(93259, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dis is more meat than we\'ve seen in a week! My people will be grateful for an actual meal. You have my gratitude.', 66263), -- Clobbering Crawlers
(93260, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those shards you found must\'ve caused de Void pollution clogging our traps. I\'m glad you removed them! De river looks much cleaner, and our trap count is back to normal... for now.\n\nMay these baskets receive Nalorakk\'s blessing and provide for de Revantusk once more.', 66263), -- Caging Crawlers
(91748, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t know what this fake bear is planning.\n\nBut it\'s better that his lodestones are destroyed.', 66263), -- Too Much Twilight
(91747, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think the trinkets were corrupted too.\n\nI\'m glad the trinkets are out of my tribe\'s claws.', 66263), -- Not Quite Nalorakk
(91813, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We meant no harm. We wanted to talk about Nalorakk.\n\nA bear showed up that says it speaks for our loa, but it feels wrong.\n\nMaybe with your help, we can sniff out a solution.', 66263), -- The Spiritpaw
(93258, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Void-tainted bodies and baskets? And some crazed crabs ambushed you? Dis is getting worse!\n\nNak\'tek found de Void polluting baskets upriver, just like what you found down here along de lakeshore. De Void ties all of our clues together! Let\'s follow that lead.', 66263), -- Crab Clues
(93257, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So word of our famine has spread?\n\n<Kahanea grimaces.>\n\nThere is no denying it.', 66263), -- Revantusk at Risk
(91389, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a thing of beauty... I am glad to know it is in the hands of someone who loves it so.', 66192), -- Clothes Make the Man
(91388, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah... beautiful, glittering manasilk. So ripe with potential.', 66192), -- Uncommon Threads
(92408, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You will find no higher quality of manasilk in all of Eversong, let alone the world.', 66192), -- Material Gains
(91386, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All right... but only because I\'m curious about the craftsmanship.\n\nIt\'ll take more than a little politeness to change my mind about these pernicious paladins.', 66192), -- Mad to Measure
(93965, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re back. Hope you found a critter you fancy.\n\nThere are plenty more where that came from. Reckon you\'ll wrangle \'em all? I leave that up to you.', 66192), -- Pet Wranglin'
(91827, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lor\'themar examines the documents carefully. After a moment, he looks up at you and allows a faint smile.>\n\nExcellent work. I knew I could count on you both.', 66192), -- No Loose Ends
(91826, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is vital information. No wonder they went to such lengths to protect it.', 66192), -- Tripwire Tango
(91824, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. With these back where they belong, their reach just got a lot shorter. I only wish we\'d uncovered who took them originally.', 66192), -- The Thieves' Trail
(91825, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. All of their most important secrets, out of their hands.', 66192), -- Dead Men Keep No Secrets
(91823, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. The less they know, the safer our people are.', 66192), -- Lines Cut, Tongues Silenced
(91822, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should be interesting.', 66192), -- The Regent's Request
(90556, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ll mourn the lost and celebrate those who survived. Thank you, $n.', 66192), -- Cutting off the Head
(90555, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All things considered, this was a good result. I wish... well. We couldn\'t save everyone, but we did save most of them. I guess that\'s as much as anyone can ask for in a situation like this.', 66192), -- Blessing of Freedom
(90553, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have wiped Eversong clean of their filth.', 66192), -- Executing the Blades
(90554, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. Even if they come crawling back, they won\'t find much.', 66192), -- Leave Ashes in Your Wake
(90570, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good--you made it. Now let\'s save those paladins.', 66192), -- To the Ruins of Deatholme
(90552, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Ruins of Deatholme. They better be alive when we get there!', 66192), -- Interrogation
(90551, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Now we can force some answers.', 66192), -- Captured Information
(90549, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, we know more. They were here at one point but they\'ve been taken, unarmed. Now we need to find out where to.', 66192), -- Signs of the Struggle
(90550, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those bastards... They\'ll pay for Sombersun\'s death!', 66192), -- A Somber Sun
(90548, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job out there. We\'ll need to find more if we\'re going to find our missing friends.', 66192), -- Twilight Missive
(90547, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The cultists are boldly showing themselves, but I don\'t see Dawnheart and the others.', 66192), -- Missing Paladins
(93384, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. The situation was hardly conducive to study.', 66192), -- Delver's Call: Collegiate Calamity
(95276, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work $n. \n\nThere\'s plenty to do now that you\'ve taken care of those issues.', 66192), -- The Last Push
(90822, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With no one left to run it, this fel operation should be done with... for now, at least.\n\nIt was a pleasure working with you, $n.', 66192), -- Murder Row: One Fel Swoop
(92870, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lil\' Scoots! Welcome back, you fuzzy menace. Thank you, champion. I\'ll return him to the cafe posthaste.\n\nAs for training... I think I shall stick to the local lynx. Far better manners.', 66192), -- Scoot Along Now
(92869, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your methods were... interesting, but I cannot deny the results. The sunwhiskers may be a little shaken up, but they\'ll recover soon enough now that they\'re back in the water where they belong. My thanks.', 66192), -- Fishy Dis-pondencies
(92868, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A dog? Yes I\'ve seen a dog, just look at what that monster\'s done to the pond!', 66192), -- He Went Thataway
(94012, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work. Even some of these handlers wouldn\'t have been able to track down that wily bird.', 66192), -- Lost Lil' Strider
(92728, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your assistance! My students should be able to handle the rest of them after a few quick lessons. We\'ll just call this a learning opportunity.', 66192), -- Dogged Disturbances
(92729, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A dog? Yes I\'ve seen a dog--look at this place! Just look at what he\'s done!', 66192), -- Hounded and Hassled
(87458, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for helping us wrap this up, $p. The value of this necklace should easily cover our old bar tab.\n\n<Tarenar gives Gidwin a sideways glance.>\n\nGiddy wasn\'t too much trouble, was he?', 66192), -- Debts Paid
(87457, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s great, $p. Thank you.\n\n<Gidwin squints at you.>\n\nDon\'t tell the elf I got cocooned, alright?', 66192), -- What We Do Best
(87456, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These look to be in good shape considering how long we left them here.\n\n<Gidwin holds up the bag of herbs.>\n\nNot sure if Fiona\'s even still looking for these, but she\'ll appreciate the uh... very late gesture.', 66192), -- Souvenirs Scattered
(87455, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<A muffled voice reaches you.>\n\nNo no, I\'ve got it! Stand back!', 66192), -- Trials and Tabulations
(89208, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It was a pleasure working with you, $n.', 66192), -- What We're Owed
(90821, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The \"Illicit Rain?\" Zaen\'s base of operations, perhaps.\n\nThat receipt mentions Suramar. The fel relics must be getting pilfered from the Broken Isles, then routed into Silvermoon through a trade line no one would suspect.\n\nClever.', 66192), -- Murder Row: Harbored Secrets
(89207, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Row will always be in danger, so long as Silvermoon turns a blind eye to us.\n\nBut for now, we\'re a little safer. Good riddance.', 66192), -- Rats Can Bite
(89206, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jaeth feels Sarvi\'s neck for a pulse, then sighs angrily.>\n\nShe\'s already gone. I know her brother. I\'ll make sure she gets returned to him.\n\nBut first, we\'ll make Aradis bleed.', 66192), -- Break and Enter
(89205, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll be surprised if Aradis isn\'t already holed up here. But if he isn\'t, I\'m sure we\'ll see him soon.\n\nWards this fancy always have alarms woven into them.', 66192), -- Cutting a Key
(89204, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice and clean. I\'ve been stealing to make ends meet since I was a kid, but I don\'t get a partner in crime very often.', 66192), -- Five Finger Discount
(89203, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He tried to take me last week too. I shanked him in the gut before he ran.\n\nI chased him, but his place down by the harbor was warded with fel magic. If Dawnblaze has a way inside, I\'ll happily finish him off.', 66192), -- Mutual Benefit
(89202, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gonna assume you have a particular type of business if you\'re asking for me by name. So spit it out.', 66192), -- Stir the Nest
(89201, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You ought to be more careful with the affairs in which you entangle yourself.', 66192), -- Outschemed
(89200, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As expected, my theory has been proven correct.\n\nThe only task that remains is breaking the final ward and removing those documents from Dawnblaze\'s possession.', 66192), -- Unraveling Wards
(89199, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Making yourself useful is a prized quality in Silvermoon. You are well on your way.', 66192), -- A Small Task
(90669, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, so the ruffian was successful.\n\nYou do certainly look capable. Let us speak, shall we?', 66192), -- Gold is Gold
(90819, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They mentioned someone named Zaen?\n\nHe\'s a well-known thug in the Row. Smuggling fel through the Silvermoon Harbor sounds exactly like his style. He doesn\'t want anyone watching him.\n\nGood work pocketing that shipping manifest.', 66192), -- Murder Row: Acting the Part
(90818, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Belath\'s expression sours more than usual.>\n\nFear drives people to desperate measures, but fel magic isn\'t a weapon to be wielded lightly.\n\nThe power comes at a cost they do not understand--nor are they trained to withstand those dangers.', 66192), -- Murder Row: Loose Lips
(90837, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hm... Legion scraps, fel dust, and evidence that both might be getting moved around the city covertly. A sanctioned fel trade would not be resorting to such measures.\n\nThen there are the mana wyrm cores we both found. Siphoned dry, but fel still clings to them.', 66192), -- Murder Row: Traces of Fel
(90835, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your arrival is timely.\n\nI will be brief: I believe there is a widespread resurgence of fel magic use happening in Silvermoon, and it must be stopped.', 66192), -- Murder Row: Rumors Abound
(92398, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The runestone hums with power again thanks to you. You have my appreciation.', 66192), -- And Then They Came
(92397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. Now for the hard part.', 66192), -- Dawnstar Defense
(92396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you\'re the one who brought the supplies. My thanks! The wards are stable now. However, there\'s another task here that could use your attention.', 66192), -- Calling in the Cavalry
(91385, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The legends are real... Eversong must be pleased with us!', 66192), -- A Ranger's Spirit
(91384, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a good start. All it takes is a handful of us putting in a little effort.', 66192), -- Recovery Mission
(91383, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My rangers are earning their keep today, that\'s for certain.', 66192), -- Tidy Up
(91350, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is what happens when there\'s no one around to sweep up!\n\nEveryone wants to adventure, but no one wants to sweep.', 66192), -- A Real Assignment
(91137, 1005, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tormenting our guests was a step too far.\n\nShe encroached on the sunbath and has paid the price for her actions.\n\nThank you, new friend of the Solaar family!', 66192), -- Lost in Light
(91090, 6, 1005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That wasn\'t so bad, was it? \n\nVal does get a bit dramatic, but you performed wonderfully.', 66192), -- Pesky Pests
(91328, 21, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Magic! Perfection! You could not be more skilled if I had wished you into existence.\n\nThat is an interesting thought. Could I have?', 66192), -- Secret Ingredients
(91271, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n! You have procured a perfectly, pleasingly, plumply proportioned pescatarian prize!\n\nJoyous day!', 66192), -- A Fish!
(87402, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What was beyond those doors was a horror. To use the Light in such a manner...\n\nThank you. We will have this place scoured with flames before it is used again.', 66192), -- The Light Provides
(87400, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll make sure this gets to a captain. And stored properly to avoid any spread.', 66192), -- Scattered in Sunbeams
(87401, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. This should get us inside the main building.', 66192), -- Gardener Mishap
(87399, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s an unfortunate task, but the creatures did not belong here. They would have put any new researchers at risk.\n\nNow to the actual problem.', 66192), -- Facing the Sun
(91349, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These poor cubs... They survived only by the grace of that strange magic!\n\nI know better than to believe in the old tales... but what else could it be?', 66192), -- The Dark Part of the Woods
(91463, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I-I\'m not worried. This is what being a Farstrider is all about!', 66192), -- To the South Tower
(92025, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Goodness! That was nearly quite the misunderstanding. I am glad you stayed your weapons long enough to hear me out.\n\nThe Scourge took much from the sin\'dorei. For some, like Amalthea, it took everything and more.\n\nNeedless to say, my studies don\'t get me invited to many parties. But they allow me, from time to time, to ease Amalthea\'s torment. To that end, I would bear any indignity.', 66192), -- Flowers for Amalthea
(92024, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Your findings leave little to the imagination. Whatever official enterprises Talandra purports to pursue, her personal affects betray a more sinister profession.>', 66192), -- House Call
(92023, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s an interesting bag of goods you\'re carrying there, friend. I don\'t suppose you\'re shopping on behalf of the \"apothecary\" in Windrunner Village?\n\nYou may wish to reconsider this course, if you value your well-being.', 66192), -- Suspicious Sundries
(92022, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There we are. See? I knew I could rely on you. We\'ve only a few steps left to manage.', 66192), -- A Venomous Vocation
(92021, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There you have it! Eight flowers. Simple enough, no? Now, I just need a few more things...\n\nWhat? I didn\'t mention that there would be a shopping list? Oh, bother. Well, nothing to it but to do it now, hrm? You don\'t seem the type to leave things half-handled.', 66192), -- Graveblossom Gardening
(91504, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The lighthouse itself was coming apart due to the increasing arcane energies, both latent and collected. How ominous indeed. I\'ll deliver a report to Regent Lord Lor\'themar straight away.\n\nThanks to you, my rangers and the town are saved. For that, please rest and drink.\n\n...the wand exploded?! I suppose we now know why it was thrown away.\n\nYou know, a bow would never spontaneously combust.', 66192), -- Arcane Amassing
(91505, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve struck fear and death into their water-spawned hearts! Well done.\n\nWe\'ll keep an eye on their base and prevent them from rebuilding.', 66192), -- Daggers in My Spine
(91494, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You can just say I had a hunch about that wand.\n\n...although, be careful. It\'s powered up now. Don\'t accidentally drop it.', 66192), -- One Elf's Trash, Another Elf's Treasure
(91495, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a relief to know they are safe and sound. I hope Varnis will be all right. I saw him scamper back, face as white as a ghost, refusing to speak. He gathered his things and left.\n\nThank you, $p. I hope no other villagers will be tempted to enter the naga\'s base!', 66192), -- Familiar Faces in Peril
(91493, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lyssara\'s suspicions proved correct. The naga must be collecting arcane magic from sources all around Eversong. We must put a stop to it, immediately.', 66192), -- Not What I Ordered
(91348, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another successful molt... We\'ll be out here in a few weeks to do it all again!', 66192), -- See a Mana 'bout a Wyrm
(91462, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a good thing we came. There are more mana wyrms here than usual.', 66192), -- To the Central Tower
(91347, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t know what to make of those big blooms... but whatever we\'re doing, the land seems pleased.', 66192); -- Strider Stampede
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(91345, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hope you like getting your hands dirty.', 66192), -- To the North Tower
(89385, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not everyone would go to such lengths for these creatures.\n\nI\'d like to give you something special, as thanks for your help. I think you have more than proven you can be entrusted with this.\n\nA hawkstrider egg. Not yet hatched, but there is a little one in there--wiggling, curious, and eager to meet the one who will raise it with love. Take care of it, and it will take good care of you in return.', 66192), -- First Step Into Parenthood
(89383, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. I\'ll have that fence reinforced so he can\'t run off again.', 66192), -- One Adventurous Hatchling
(89386, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, they\'ll have many a happy night\'s sleep on this! You have my thanks.', 66192), -- A Roost-ed Development
(89384, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve been told frog legs taste like a curious blend of fish and poultry. I... think I will leave that fine dining experience to the hawkstriders, however. Thank you for your help!', 66192), -- A Hungry Flock
(91452, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It might seem like a small thing, but the small things add up.', 66192), -- Range of Knowledge
(91342, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The sweeping will still need to get done, but at least now no one will be attacked.', 66192), -- If You Want It Done Right
(94371, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It was good of you to check on me, but I\'m committed to the Farstriders!', 66192), -- A Ranger's Dream
(87398, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. I am sure there will be more figures like him in the future, but at least for today, this port is safe thanks to you.\n\nI hope I can count on you again in the future, partner.', 66192), -- Smuggler Showdown
(87396, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. The naga may have been handled, but our work is far from complete.\n\nTideborne Freight continues to pull the strings, and it is time we sever their control.', 66192), -- Dead to Rights
(87397, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did what was required. If the cargo is gone, that is a victory--but our work is far from over.\n\nThe Tideborne must still answer for their actions.', 66192), -- Cargo Collateral
(87395, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Unstable arcana and naga? This is hardly just smuggling--it\'s a disaster waiting to unfold.\n\nThe Tideborne are dabbling in matters better left untouched. It seems it is now our responsibility to see it resolved before it becomes an issue.', 66192), -- Below the Brine
(87394, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There it is--caught in the act.\n\nDisposing of cargo into the ocean? Clearly they are erasing evidence, which can only mean one thing: we are closing in on something significant.', 66192), -- Supplier Surveillance
(87393, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'But of course, they would prefer to keep prying eyes at bay.\n\nThey are guarding something. Now, we must uncover precisely what it is.', 66192), -- Warranted Search
(87392, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, a note on \"special cargo.\" How delightfully subtle--about as discreet as a goblin\'s pyrotechnics.\n\nIt seems the Tideborne are entangled in this mess, and we have little choice but to wade in after them. If that means diving into the depths, so be it.', 66192), -- Cargo Conspiracy
(90544, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Luma nudges a small reward into your hand, as if in appreciation for your help.\n\nPerhaps there is no reason to be concerned over the amount of stolen items in the treasure pile after all.>', 66192), -- Thief at Bark
(88979, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A dog, a lynx, and now a ruined journal. Truly, I\'ve seen lesser misfortunes in my day.\n\n<Meledor pinches the slobbery journal between his fingers.>\n\nIt seems the journal\'s fate was sealed long before we laid eyes on it. It is quite beyond saving. Once again, my faith in anything other than arcane precision has proven... misplaced.', 66192), -- Caught Red-Handed
(88977, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful--more glowing projections and angry spirits, yet still no journal.\n\nStep aside. I\'m ending this nonsense and tracking it properly.', 66192), -- Reenact the Crime
(88978, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That fool... That absolute fool.', 66192), -- Tracking the Trail
(91301, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah... so the boy has chosen at last. He has heart--too much perhaps.\n\nYes. This will be recorded and honored. You\'ve done more than deliver a message--you\'ve helped shape a life. Thank you.', 66192), -- How to Train Your Protege
(91284, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow... I can\'t believe I actually got all three recommendations. They all said such kind things, but now I feel even more torn than before!\n\nDo you think... perhaps you could help me choose?', 66192), -- A Path Not Yet Chosen
(91292, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm, it seems you have a bit more talent than I anticipated.\n\nThis staff is properly charged. Well done, though I\'m sure you barely broke a sweat.\n\nTake this recommendation, and remember--the arcane demands respect, not just power.', 66192), -- A Test of the Arcane
(91288, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well now, look at that. Clean cuts, no mess... maybe the kid\'s got more fire than I thought.\n\nHere, take this recommendation. Tell them a Farstrider never forgets who earns their place--and to keep their aim sharp. We\'ll be watching.', 66192), -- A Test of the Hunt
(91291, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive! You\'ve got more in you than I expected.\n\nYou\'ve proven your strength, honor, and determination--qualities every Blood Knight must possess.\n\nTake this recommendation and wear it with pride. The order is always looking for those who are worthy.', 66192), -- A Test of Blood
(87002, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve defeated me today, but mark my words... I will rise again, and you\'ll regret crossing me. I am Tytalor Goldenblade, and this defeat is but temporary!', 66192), -- Academic Aspirations
(86998, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must say, I underestimated you. It seems there\'s more to you than just flailing around.', 66192), -- Training Arc
(86997, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shocking. Truly shocking. Perhaps there\'s some truth to you after all--but only perhaps.', 66192), -- Spellbook Scuffle
(86522, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This was an impossible mission. We won\'t forget the sacrifices that bought us a fighting chance.\n\nStill, I know not every victory feels worthy of celebration. When war forces us to choose between friendship and duty, there are many who would be unable to act.\n\nWe will not squander the opportunity you\'ve given us. Now, our counter offensive begins.', 66192), -- Daylight is Breaking
(86521, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s over. We can breathe, if only for a moment.', 66192), -- Nexus-Point Xenas: Eclipse
(86520, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He\'s already here. We have to stop him.', 66192), -- Hunt the Light
(86519, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lothraxion\'s going to tear the Nexus-Points apart, even if it costs us Silvermoon!', 66192), -- Abyssus, Abyssum
(86518, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you alright? I must have missed something. Why did Decimus bother helping us at all? They could have betrayed us at any time. It doesn\'t make any sense...', 66192), -- The Mantle of Predation
(86516, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good hunting. With the ultradons dead, we may just be able to get out of here alive.', 66192), -- All Become Prey
(86517, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This isn\'t right. Hieron didn\'t come here to die. The Light should protect people, not lead them to their deaths.\n\n<Arator seems lost in thought.>\n\nThank you. I\'ll make sure to give his journal to the others.', 66192), -- Vanished in the Void
(86515, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Soon we\'ll have the Mantle of Predation and no longer need Decimus.\n\nDo not mistake their usefulness for allegiance as Alleria has.', 66192), -- Hollow Hunger
(86514, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve never known Lothraxion to be careless like this. Throwing lives away, charging in blind--doesn\'t he know he\'s not leading an army here? \n\nAt least you\'ve done your part. Let\'s try to salvage the mission.', 66192), -- Lady of the Pit
(86513, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is what my mother has battled on her own for all these years? I won\'t let her shoulder that burden alone anymore.', 66192), -- Face the Tide
(86512, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you sense it? Every beast here either fears you or wants to kill you. Even their mistress cannot ignore you now.', 66192), -- The Harvest
(86511, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t like dividing our forces. Not when this much is at stake.\n\nLet\'s not rush in like Lothraxion. See what Decimus knows. I\'d rather not hunt a domanaar unprepared.', 66192), -- Edge of the Abyss
(90571, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There you have it--simply steal the Mantle from Terminas. I\'d recommend acting quickly. Who knows when Terminas will return to the Obscurion Citadel.\n\nA shame about Ciphus. I was planning to devour him myself once I\'d fattened him up.', 66192), -- The Lay of the Beast
(86510, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Comfortable? So nice to see someone appreciate my hospitality.\n\nNow I suppose we must discuss business before your glowing friend has another tantrum.', 66192), -- Domus Penumbra
(86509, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Guests are a rare treat for a domanaar. Especially ones that come of their own accord.', 66192), -- Friend or Fiend
(86545, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Decimus is a far more capable domanaar than they\'ve been letting on.', 66192), -- The Light's Brand
(86544, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What was that...?', 66192), -- Post-Mortem
(89249, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even the power of a naaru wasn\'t enough...', 66192), -- Overwhelmed
(86542, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Everything I could muster. It was simply... devoured.', 66192), -- Flicker in the Dark
(88768, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope Xal\'atath was watching. It\'ll be her turn soon.', 66192), -- Agents of Darkness
(86540, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is taking too long! Every wasted moment brings us closer to ruin!', 66192), -- Third, Blow It Up
(86541, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A mortal, receptive to outside ideas. Truly exemplary. No need to thank me.\n\nThough, perhaps you\'d want to free me of this bondage? I\'m feeling a bit chafed by the Light about now.\n\nNo? Oh well.', 66192), -- Just In Case...
(86539, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A naaru, imprisoned. The Light shall give these monsters no mercy.', 66192), -- A Naaru!
(86537, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Xal\'atath.\n\nLet us see this final message.', 66192), -- Network Insecurity
(86538, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Potent. I can feel the energy--radiant. Glorious.', 66192), -- Second, The Fuel
(86530, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. The same make I remember.\n\nNow, the catalyst.', 66192), -- First, The Shells
(86528, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve seen one of these before. Ethereals use them to encrypt communications.\n\nExcellent find, $n.', 66192), -- A Cracked Holokey
(86531, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They will try to rebuild, but we won\'t give them the chance.', 66192), -- Work Disruption
(86536, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If Xal\'atath was mortal, then she is all the more monstrous for all that she has done. For becoming what she is now.\n\nOur long battle comes to an end on this world. I swear it.', 66192), -- Reliable Enemies
(86565, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done good work, $n.', 66192), -- No Prayer for the Wicked
(86561, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lothraxion scowls.>\n\nDespicable stuff. Alleria has explained her plan to me, but I\'m not sure I agree.', 66192), -- A Strange, Different World
(86562, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There seems to be creatures here both bestial and magical. \n\nThe Void is drawn to violence. I have seen countless worlds drown in it. \n\nCould the savagery of the beasts here have brought the Void in naturally?', 66192), -- Dancing with Death
(86559, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The rest of the void elves have been dispersed to set up camps or scout.\n\nI am... conflicted over Alleria\'s presence. Her skills and experience are unspeakably valuable, and yet...\n\nThe Void in her is so strong... I worry. Keep an eye on her.\n\nThe Void can NEVER be trusted.', 66192), -- The Far, Far Frontier
(86557, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vile beasts. Did you sense it?\n\nThey all reek of Void.', 66192), -- A Matter of Strife and Death
(86558, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The void elves risk corruption, and yet are most suited to understanding the world around us. We need their expertise, but cannot trust them.\n\nIt irks me, but I have already sent for more scouts.', 66192), -- Save a Piece of Mind
(86549, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This... this power! I have never felt the Void like this. \n\nAll-consuming.', 66192), -- No Fear of the Dark
(86543, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That could have gone better. \n\nThen again, Rommath hasn\'t killed me, yet. It could have gone worse.', 66192), -- Magisters' Terrace: Homecoming
(29518, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s a good bit of scrap here. Thanks for your help. It\'ll be a big help when I refit the steam tonks.$B$BPlease take this as a reward for your help.', 66192), -- Rearm, Reuse, Recycle
(29511, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job getting those tonks back online. Here are those tickets I promised.', 66192), -- Talkin' Tonks
(86833, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$p, that did not go as I hoped, to say the least.\n\nI\'d hoped he would be able to see... to accept that he could still change.\n\nBut it doesn\'t look like he\'s open to that--at least, not now.', 66192), -- A Bulwark Remade
(86832, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We certainly did some good in the Burning Steppes, $p, and recovered the fragments of Turalyon\'s shield.\n\nArator seems excited to see it reforged.', 66192), -- A Worthy Forge
(91726, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a tragic story, but maybe something better can be made o\' it with those fragments of Turalyon\'s shield.\n\nPerhaps it can be restored--along with our friend.', 66192), -- Unstoppable Force
(86829, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These fragments you\'ve been recovering might be the most important relics of our journey, $p.', 66192), -- A Landmark Moment
(86830, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You killed many of them, but I watched even more run away. \n\nLet\'s hope they never return.', 66192), -- A True Horde of Dark Horde
(86831, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $p! I believe this will save many lives across the region. With no warlord to rally them, the Dark Horde should fall apart.', 66192), -- Warriors Without a Warlord
(86828, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$p, Arator--good to see you. I believe I have a solution to our problem.', 66192), -- Not Just a Troll's Bane
(91842, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did ye destroy their weapons racks?\n\nAye, that\'ll do. We\'ve bought everyone nearby a few months of peace while they resupply.', 66192), -- Disarm the Dark Horde
(86826, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did ye get Faol\'s relic?\n\nI hope that old priest knows what he\'s doing.', 66192), -- Nagosh the Scarred
(86827, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That gave \'em a kick in the pants! \n\nSee if any of \'em volunteer to lead their warbands now, after that humiliation!', 66192), -- Due Recognition
(91391, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Arator, $p--thanks fer coming. Plenty o\' Dark Horde in there.', 66192), -- Still Scouting
(86825, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As we defeat their leaders, the Dark Horde presence throughout the Burning Steppes will continue to splinter.\n\nMar\'kag was the first to fall. This was a good first step.', 66192), -- Faithful Servant, Faithless Cause
(86824, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope that this might demoralize some of these soldiers out of their misguided devotion to a failed cause.\n\nRegardless, I am glad those banners are not flying any longer.', 66192), -- None Left Standing
(86823, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps, in the face of the death of their comrades, others will see sense as I did. At least those you killed won\'t dishonor themselves any longer.', 66192), -- The Dark Horde
(86822, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems we have more to do here than just finding a relic.\n\nThis area is overrun with a group that calls themselves the \"Dark Horde,\" and we are going to put a stop to their activities.', 66192), -- One Final Relic
(89338, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $p. We\'ll get these reforged into tools, and distribute them to the people.', 66192), -- Gathering Plowshares
(86846, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! This will help the people of Hammerfall help themselves.', 66192), -- Resupplying Our Suppliers
(91000, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $p. Things are starting to look better.', 66192), -- A Humble Servant
(86845, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An\'she has guided you to us, $p. Care to join us in our work?', 66192), -- The Sunwalker Path
(86902, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With those relics, they should be able to sustain the ritual for much longer.\n\nAnd we can attend to other matters.', 66192), -- Relinquishing Relics
(92136, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quickly, $p. Let us get these distributed!', 66192), -- Infusion of Hope
(86844, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These weapons of the Light shall serve a much greater purpose from this day forward.\n\nI hope that may be true as well for Aelyse--the Scarlet champion Arator showed mercy to.\n\nI told her to begin by surrendering herself to Calia Menethil at the Sunwell.', 66192), -- Light Repurposed
(86843, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work.\n\nPerhaps one day, the Scarlet Monastery can be a place that truly serves the Light, but for now our time is limited and our focus must remain on the Sunwell.', 66192), -- Light Miswielded
(86842, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here we are. Let\'s deal with these Scarlets.', 66192), -- Scarlet Power
(86841, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust you found what you needed, $p?', 66192), -- Relics of Paladins Past
(86840, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. You\'ve thinned their ranks enough that we\'ll be able to maintain the defenses, with the help we have from our... allies.\n\nNow, Faol has told me about your need for relics.', 66192), -- Flickering Hope
(86839, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Light\'s Hope, $p. \n\nMost of the paladins that defended these grounds were called by the Light. I\'ve had to reach out to the Ebon Blade for support, or the Scourge would have overrun this holy place.', 66192), -- Relics of Light's Hope
(86838, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had hoped that seeing the rest of the Vanguard focused on the Sunwell, it would give him a goal that was bigger than his pain and lead him away from his anger. Instead, he belittles my solution.\n\nThank you, $n, for doing it in his stead. It was necessary to keep the Voidstorm at bay.', 66192), -- Renewal for the Weary
(86837, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nnnghhh... It is so painfully bright here, don\'t you think? \n\nAhh, you were able to convince him. Thank you.', 66192), -- Meet at the Sunwell
(89193, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for coming, $p. I need your help, as do many of our priests and paladins.\n\nOne paladin in particular.', 66192), -- Arator
(91084, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'When Halduron burst into a war council shouting about hidden worlds and ancient warriors, I thought he had gone mad. But now that I\'ve seen the haranir with my own eyes...\n\nWe are lucky to have them as potential allies. And lucky to have you, I\'d say, in brokering that relationship.\n\nThere is more for us to do. But I\'ve no doubt that the Hara\'ti will prove vital allies to Silvermoon in the days to come.', 66192), -- Looming Shadows
(86898, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For the first time in generations, the haranir walk upon the surface of Aln\'hara\'s creation. Time will tell how her creation receives us in turn.\n\nThe fighting is far from over. The Void claws at your gates and threatens your people. But know this, my friend: from this day forward, any threat that encroaches upon Aln\'hara\'s bounty will have the Hara\'ti to contend with, be it here or deep below the earth.', 66192), -- Rise of the Haranir
(86897, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is over. Though the Lightbloom may never fully recede, its mastermind has been driven back into the rootway. With the frenzy quelled, and the surrounding forests warded against its advance, we can rest assured that Eversong will not suffer the Lightbloom\'s spread any longer.\n\nWe\'ve done it. We\'ve won!', 66192), -- Quelling the Frenzy
(86896, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Between you and our new haranir allies, my rangers have plenty of ferocious examples to follow. I\'ll have to consider teaching some of your techniques at the Retreat.', 66192), -- Light Finds a Way
(86894, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The haranir are always mighty. But with the goddess\'s gift shining upon us, we are unstoppable.', 66192), -- The Gift of Aln'hara
(86892, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I... I cannot believe it. My kin on the surface, standing shoulder to shoulder with surface-dwellers, and wielding the magics of Aln...\n\n<Orweyna sets her jaw and flashes you a smile.>\n\nBut we do not have time for sentiment. We must bring Ruia to justice, and end this frenzy.', 66192), -- Survive
(86887, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most of the Farstriders have retreated to our position. Those that remain are prepared to slip away once the ritual begins.\n\nWe\'re out of time. It\'s now or never.', 66192), -- Expeditious Retreat
(86891, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve done all we can.\n\nNow all that\'s left is to defend the Magisters, and hope that this is enough to stop the frenzy from spreading any farther.', 66192), -- A Last Resort
(86885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Damn it all. For every rootway you torch, two more crop up elsewhere. It\'s like they\'re self-perpetuating, spreading in the span of moments.\n\nI don\'t think we can solve this with arrows and magic, even with Orweyna\'s help. We don\'t have enough Alndust, nor enough haranir to prevent the spread of this frenzy.', 66192), -- Stem the Tides
(86884, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a shame to see something born of Harandar wreaking such havoc on a place like this. These roots may not cradle Aln\'hara, but they grow toward her all the same.', 66192), -- Cull and Burn
(86883, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To think that while we toiled below, the Lightbloom would spread so aggressively in Eversong.\n\nDamn it all! Every victory we win reveals rising danger.', 66192), -- The Frenzied March
(86890, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Azeroth needs our help. I will not stand idly by while she is overwhelmed.\n\nI know you will not, either.', 66192), -- Tell the People What You Have Seen
(86880, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These artifacts pale in importance to the lives of those involved here... but it is good to have them back.', 66192), -- Our Beloved, Returned
(86877, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wish we could save everyone, but...\n\nA gruesome but necessary task.', 66192), -- Righteous Pruning
(86881, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I pray this will help us all.', 66192), -- At the Root
(86874, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Though the Lightbloom remains vibrant where it has already taken root, the Alndust-aided attacks seem effective in limiting additional growth and propagation. For now, the rest of Harandar should be safe from further spread.', 66192), -- Culling the Light
(86867, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now we can begin.', 66192), -- Into the Lightbloom
(86882, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is so much more than what the Rootwarden said. How has the Lightbloom spread so much, and so quickly?', 66192), -- Alndust in Right Hands
(94677, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is troubling news. The Lightbloom hasn\'t seemed to affect any haranir thus far. Has it somehow infested the Rootwarden? Or is this his pride speaking? He\'s always been a zealous one, but...\n\nWe must move quickly.', 66192), -- The Missing Rootwarden
(86866, 1034, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Alndust may not be able to recover someone who has fully fallen to the Lightbloom, but it should be able to inoculate those from further corruption. That must be enough.', 66192), -- Can We Heal This?
(86865, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have left our homes. We will return.', 66192), -- In Search of the Problem
(86862, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thought I would never see this with my own eyes... and yet here we are.\n\nMake this worth it.', 66192), -- The Greater They Aln
(86861, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That must be enough.', 66192), -- Herding Manifestations
(86860, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done.', 66192), -- Before They Grow
(86859, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We might have a chance with this. I\'ll be able to coat my weapons with this and craft a powerful poison.', 66192), -- Grinding Out a Solution
(86858, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another soul saved.\n\nThis is why I do this, $p. All my sacrifices, shutting myself from the voice of the goddess, is worth it for each soul I rescue from the grasp of the rift.', 66192), -- The Madness Roots Deep
(86857, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That manifestation is one of the purest forms of Aln madness that resides here. My ward will distract it only for so long. We must move quickly.', 66192), -- Descent into the Rift
(86856, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot hear the voice of the goddess.\n\nI hate it.\n\nHow does Amarakk live like this?', 66192), -- Dampening the Call
(86851, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My hands tingle where the Alndust touches. A curious feeling... not unwelcome.\n\nThe honored Shul\'ka told me how to manipulate the Alndust to protect haranir in the rift. It seemed difficult, but with its magic swelling in me, I feel that it should be doable.', 66192), -- The Foundation of Aln
(86855, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is sobering to see the effects of the rift on my peoples. But Amarakk\'s interference has given me unintended hope.\n\nI must go into the rift to search for Hagar\'s answer, and with the Shul\'ka\'s help, I may even survive this ordeal.', 66192), -- Consequences of Our Duty
(86836, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have given up my connection to the goddess to protect my people from the dangers of the Rift of Aln. I do not believe anyone should ever go there without knowing what you risk. Haranir will succumb and die without protection.', 66192), -- The Hunter Awaits
(86864, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In the end, we must figure this out for ourselves.', 66192), -- Watch the Den
(86930, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We return to where we started, but this time you have been blessed by the goddess and we have evidence that the spread of the Lightbloom may be stalled!\n\nThe way forward is not yet clear, but I feel that we are closer.', 66192), -- To Sow the Seed
(86944, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Eonka and her seeds are not affected by the Lightbloom. Incredible! Could there be something about the rift that keeps the Lightbloom in check?', 66192), -- Seeds of the Rift
(86973, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tough, but needed work. May this slow the spread until we can find a way to stop it entirely.', 66192), -- Halting Harm in Har'mara
(86942, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done, then. I grieve that this was necessary, but the corruption needed to be pruned before it could spread further.', 66192), -- Culling the Spread
(89034, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. May Har\'mara return to the peaceful oasis it was when we arrived.', 66192), -- Burning Bitterblooms
(86910, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Koozat is the least of our troubles right now. The Lightbloom has arrived. Har\'mara is under attack!', 66192), -- Koozat's Trample
(86956, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So there are no signs of Lightbloom yet in their villages? Meeka seems unchanged as well, and states that the rutaani never act in the manner of the Light-crazed.\n\nThis is both promising and frustrating.\n\nI am glad that it hasn\'t yet spread that far, but I suspect we shall find more soon.', 66192), -- The Traveling Flowers
(86914, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sometimes harmony and friendship are helped by small acts of service.\n\nI hope that the rutaani and fungarians here have come to see you as an ally.', 66192), -- Tending to Har'mara
(86913, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Har\'mara. I am glad to see you well and whole after the trials.\n\nThis village is the home of Hagar and many others who call Harandar their home.', 66192), -- A Hut in Har'mara
(86912, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You awaken. Good. Now that you have seen our past, I have brought you to my home, to see my hope for the future.\n\nHere in Har\'mara, we live in harmony with two of the local peoples: the rutaani, and the fungarians. It is my dream that this partnership will spread to the rest of Harandar.\n\nYou should get to know them as well, and see the peace that we have created together.', 66192), -- Down the Rootways
(90095, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now you know how the Hara\'ti came to walk amongst the roots.\n\nOne final trial remains--the most difficult, but most important, of them all.\n\nHagar awaits you, and will guide you through the next challenge.', 66192), -- Echo of the Call
(90094, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have proven yourself a capable hunter like our ancestors of old. But simply being the strongest did not prove succor enough for the minds of our people.', 66192), -- Echo of the Hunt
(86911, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have made it through the first of the trials, but the real test is yet to come.', 66192), -- Echoes and Memories
(86907, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the Den of Echoes. Within the caves beyond, you will find ancient paintings which tell the story of the haranir.\n\nPerhaps you will learn something, if you survive. May Aln\'hara be on your side.', 66192), -- The Den of Echoes
(86929, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To stay among us, it must be proven that the goddess has indeed called you to her aid. \n\nYou will undergo trials at the Den of Echoes, a holy place for our people.', 66192), -- The Council Assembles
(86901, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tread carefully, $n. The haranir are formidable and on edge over our arrival.\n\nThe Council has convened and is ready to hear Orweyna\'s words. Hopefully she will be able to convince them that the Lightbloom is a threat and that their help is needed.', 66192), -- The Rift and the Den
(86900, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outsiders are not permitted in Harandar. Orweyna has broken our most sacred of laws.\n\nYou are not welcome here, stranger.', 66192), -- To Har'athir
(86899, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made it. For a moment I wasn\'t sure you would. Don\'t worry--that nauseous feeling will pass.\n\nWe stand in the deep roots of Amirdrassil. My home lies beyond.\n\nLet us see what welcome awaits.', 66192), -- The Root Cause
(89402, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to see you again, friend.\n\nWould that we were meeting under less fraught circumstances.', 66192), -- Harandar
(91087, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lor\'themar raises an eyebrow and frowns slightly. You can tell he is fighting back exasperation and anger.>\n\nThis is a... very unexpected turn of events. Yet still more will unfold in front of us, I\'m sure.', 66192), -- Reports Returned
(91062, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad I found you. Zul\'jarra let me know you would be searching this area for Zul\'jan, but this land is still so unfamiliar to me.\n\nIf you have found him and are finished enjoying the party, we should return to Silvermoon.', 66192), -- Broken Bridges
(86693, 1034, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It did not occur to me dat what we would be celebratin\' would be... me.\n\nThere has been no hash\'ey among de Amani since before de elf and human war thousands of years ago.\n\nIt is a great honor, but one I am not sure I have yet earned.\n\nI will strive to live up to it.', 66192), -- De Legend of de Hash'ey
(86692, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zul\'jarra snorts and spits out a viscous wad of blood, broken tooth included.>\n\nIt is done.', 66192), -- Blade Shattered
(91001, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mor\'duun may laugh now, holed up in de Sanctum.\n\nBut we will get de last laugh.', 66192), -- Clear de Way
(86685, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was good.\n\nBut I still thirst for more.', 66192), -- Chip and Shatter
(86687, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The sight of de loa fightin\' by their side has filled our warriors with hope.\n\nDey remember dat dey are Amani!', 66192), -- Conduit Crisis
(86686, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I look forward to Lor\'themar\'s expression when I report back.\n\n<A slight smile creeps across Liadrin\'s blood-spotted jaw.>\n\nIt\'s bound to be worth more than my inevitable reprimanding.', 66192), -- Light Indiscriminate
(86684, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zul\'jarra\'s piercing eyes survey the battlefield. She mutters under her breath what you can only imagine is troll profanities. You hear her say \"Jan\" among them.>\n\nDe battlefield is full of bodies. De bodies of my people. But there are more still in de fight!\n\nThere is time to turn de tide!', 66192), -- The Blade's Edge
(86683, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now dis will be a fight!', 66192), -- Hash'ey Away
(91958, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Heh.\n\nWe won against Nalorakk. We passed de last trial.\n\nMy tribe will sing songs and tell stories of dis day for generations.', 66192), -- Den of Nalorakk: Unforgiven
(86682, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do not pity Lilaju--I was around her age when I took my place as leader of de Amani.\n\nI am proud of her. She is stickin\' up for herself and her tribe.\n\nShe gave us what we needed. And I will not go back on my promise of helping her.', 66192), -- Den of Nalorakk: Waking de Bear
(86681, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I love my brother. We are as de day is to de night. But even so, as children we were close.\n\nZul\'jan is smart but he doesn\'t understand. A victory means nothin\' if there is no one left to celebrate it.\n\nHe is supposed to be my right hand, not a pain in de neck.\n\nI hope I have not left Zul\'jan without guidance too long to turn him around.', 66192), -- Den of Nalorakk: A Taste of Vengeance
(86666, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many dead...', 66192), -- In the Shadow of Rebirth
(90772, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, hash\'ura.\n\nJan\'alai is reborn! And we have her blessin\'.\n\n<Zul\'jarra closes her eyes and briefly enjoys the feeling of the flame against her face.>', 66192), -- The Flames Rise Higher
(86665, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fittin\' that de last test be facin\' my own doubt. About my leadership and my choices.\n\nIt felt good. As if de doubt melted away.\n\nAnd I gotta say... I never seen flames so fit and handsome.\n\n<Zul\'jarra, despite it all, laughs heartily and claps you on the shoulder.>', 66192), -- Face in the Fire
(86664, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zul\'jarra brushes some ash off her shoulder.>\n\nJan\'alai\'s flame... it has taken de doubts from my heart and given dem form.\n\nI... was not prepared for dat.\n\nWhat else do they have in store?', 66192), -- Seer or Sear
(86663, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zul\'jarra watches the flames dance in the coals. A small smile creeps up on her face. She balls her fists and flexes her arms.>\n\nI think dis trial is starting now.\n\nWhatever it throws at me... I\'ll be ready!', 66192), -- Embers to a Flame
(86808, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '\"Purify yaself, and it will rise.\"\n\nI shoulda brought Zul\'jan. He was always good with riddles.', 66192), -- The Riddled Speaker
(86661, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '\"Eccentric loa speaker.\"\n\nHeh. That sounds familiar. I guess dey are all like dat.', 66192), -- Coals of a Dead Loa
(92084, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Like Akil\'zon, Halazzi was watching. Waiting.\n\nHe never gave up on de Witherbark.', 66192), -- Halazzi's Guile
(86659, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Findin\' Halazzi and de hash\'ey shrines has taught me patience. And forced me to think through my obstacles, instead of cuttin\' my way through dem.\n\nI wish Zul\'jan were here. He would be proud of me for gainin\' some brains. Heh.', 66192), -- Breaching the Mist
(86660, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So that\'s why the Vilebranch wanted de Witherbark--to please de Twilight\'s Blade by givin\' dem more soldiers.\n\nUndead soldiers. Obedient soldiers.\n\nAnd we have already lost too many.', 66192), -- Rescue from the Shadows
(86658, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zul\'jarra spits on the ground.>\n\nDisgusting. Dey deserve to be brought back and killed a hundred times.\n\nI hope whatever loa awaits dem in de afterlife swallows dem whole and grinds dem with its back teeth.', 66192), -- The Crypt in the Mist
(86657, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De Vilebranch have caused my people sufferin\' for too long.\n\n<Zul\'jarra glares in fury at the nearby Vilebranch village of Maisara.>\n\nIt\'s been a long time coming, but now\'s de time to deal with them.', 66192), -- Shadebasin Watch
(86809, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zul\'jarra\'s eyes are closed. She seems lost in thought.>\n\nDey were here all along. It was my grandfather\'s fault dey would not answer.\n\n<She nods her head and sighs.>\n\nMy grandfather broke dis. It is up to me to fix it. It is de only way to save my people.', 66192), -- Test of Conviction
(86656, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That voice...\n\nYou heard it too, $n?', 66192), -- Brutal Feast
(89334, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zul\'jarra takes one of the heads by the hair and admires your handiwork.>\n\nNow we\'re talking their language. Now dey know dat de Amani are stronger! \n\nSome may linger, but when we defeat de Twilight\'s Blade, we will come back for dem.\n\nKeep de heads. I have an idea how dey might be useful later.', 66192), -- Ahead of the Issue
(86655, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De shrines are lit.\n\nNow what do we do?', 66192), -- De Ancient Path
(86654, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Hopefully that clears the path to the shrines and the temple enough for our purposes.', 66192), -- Gnarldin Bashing
(86653, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dis path is thick with gnarldin.\n\n<Zul\'jarra smiles broadly.>\n\nI hope dey try to stop us. I can sharpen my blade on dey bones.', 66192), -- The Path of the Amani
(86652, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hash\'ey? Has uncle lost his sense?\n\nIt is a tale for children. Maybe if this were de old days, generations ago, before de elves arrived...\n\nBut if de last chance we got is to try to speak to the loa, then I will try.', 66192), -- Left in the Shadows
(86723, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is... much you do not know about us and de loa.', 66192), -- Isolation
(86722, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tokobo\'ne na Amani\'Zar, $n. Welcome to Amani\'Zar.\n\nBecause you are my guests, my people will not harm you... unless I say so.\n\nDon\'t give me a reason, yeah?', 66192), -- Heart of the Amani
(86720, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zul\'jarra seethes with rage.>\n\nMor\'duun is playin\' with us. He coulda stayed and destroyed de city outright.\n\nIf chaos is de Twilight\'s Blade\'s plan, we need to prepare.', 66192), -- Break the Blade
(86712, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De troops we armed have killed a great many Twilight\'s Blade.\n\nSome survived and made their way here.\n\nWe lost a few, but I think de sacrifice was worth it.', 66192), -- The Amani Stand Strong
(86718, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The next to fall will be Mor\'duun.', 66192), -- Twilight Bled
(86715, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should slow them down--at least for the moment.', 66192), -- Rituals Cut Short
(86721, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We lost so much of it...\n\nWe could have blacked out de sky with ballista bolts!\n\nBut dis still may be enough. It will have to be!', 66192), -- Everything We Worked For
(86716, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good.\n\nNow we have teeth to bite back with.', 66192), -- Armed by Light
(86719, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Eagles... loa... we don\'t have time to dwell on de spirits of the past.', 66192), -- Important Amani
(86717, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You cleared de way, but Mor\'duun continues to keep us scrambling and off-balance.\n\nWe\'re gonna need as many lightwood weapons as we can get to end this.', 66192), -- Show Us Your Worth
(91980, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You return with her thorn? Ah yes, a fine trophy. Well done.', 66337), -- WANTED: Hellebora's Thorn
(91970, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You return in one piece? Not bad, outsider. Not bad.', 66337), -- WANTED: Gelatonius
(92010, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you return. And with glowing stalks to adorn my dinner table. Well done.', 66337), -- WANTED: Slewstalk's Stalks
(86810, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m quite certain these samples will not be enough, but it is a good start!  Check back later I may have some more tasks.', 66337), -- Harvesting the Void
(91251, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope this one, at least, did not suffer in her final moments. Rest well, Neydra.', 66337), -- Prey: Neydra the Starving (Hard)
(91236, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have given her the rest she so dearly needed.', 66337), -- Prey: Lieutenant Blazewing (Hard)
(92178, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For so many years, I\'ve dedicated my life to these magical pursuits.\n\nThis next chapter will be something to behold.', 66337), -- Practical Magic
(92177, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While you collect more anguish, I will experiment with this power\'s potential.', 66337), -- One Hero's Prey
(91117, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You smell like a corpse and have that distant look in your eyes one gets from spending too much time around death knights. I assume your hunt was a success?', 66337), -- Prey: Knight-Errant Bloodshatter (Normal)
(93850, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The pain, the fear... I can feel that music washing it all away.\n\nThank you, friend.', 66337), -- Windrunner Spire: Haunting Melodies
(93086, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us begin.', 66337), -- To the Sanctum!
(93043, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can assure you that it will seldom be this easy.', 66337), -- When Predator Becomes Prey
(92945, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One fool\'s trap is another elf\'s treasure.', 66337), -- The Power of Anguish
(92926, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see your interest has been piqued. \n\nExcellent.', 66337), -- Prey: Astalor's Initiative
(95114, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at you.... following directions already. \n\nExcellent.', 66337), -- Prey: A Crimson Summons
(95245, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Back so soon? Impressive!', 66337), -- Midnight: World Tour
(91932, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quite acceptable!\n\nYou may yet prove a glorious addition to the acolytes of abundance.', 66263), -- The Abundant Awakening
(91930, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is time to learn from de master himself.', 66263), -- The Abundant Lands
(93942, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a Spark of Radiance.\n\nEvery week, one of these sparks will appear while on your adventures. In its current state, it\'s rather useless, but acquiring more will allow you to craft powerful items. Reagents like these are malleable, robust, and the prize for many crafters.\n\nThis is a unique crafting material that can help an item achieve expertise beyond that of mortal ability.', 66263), -- Spark of Radiance
(93889, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well to navigate the Court without being swallowed by its politics. Silvermoon needs those who can act with purpose, not those lost in the machinery of ambition.', 66263), -- Midnight: Saltheril's Soiree
(94816, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your assistance. Please accept this token as thanks.', 66263), -- Fine Fashion Funding
(93930, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I half expected you to run back home in tears! I hope you had a stunning time.', 66263), -- Courting Success
(90574, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your deeds honor us, $n. You have fought well this day.', 66263), -- Fortify the Runestones: Blood Knights
(90782, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The woman seems wary of you, but nonetheless bows at your approach.>\n\nFriend? Hope of us.', 66263), -- The Nethersent
(92607, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The shade wasn\'t trying to torment me--it was in agony. I\'d made it in the depths of my loneliness, and it reflected that: bound to me, unable to exist alone, trying to provide comfort it couldn\'t while stuck as my shadow.\n\nI\'d looked outwards to deal with my loneliness. Finding the Void, becoming ren\'dorei, following the others here... I thought if I just found the right place, I wouldn\'t feel this way. \n\nBut I was wrong. It was always inside me. I couldn\'t cast it out, only embrace it.', 66263), -- And Carve New Shapes
(92606, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Remarkable. This chisel is not made to carve stone or metal, but the Void itself. It can free me from this shade.', 66263), -- Take Up Your Gift
(92605, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. Give me a moment to powder this and we\'ll soon have the pigment we require.', 66263), -- Honest as Bone
(92604, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope it wasn\'t too much trouble. This sort of work was always beyond me. I never could grasp the more violent Void arts.', 66263), -- Speak in Blood
(92603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for accompanying me. I didn\'t really have anyone else to ask.\n\nThe other ren\'dorei... The Void changes many things, but I feel just as out of place in Telogrus as I did in Silvermoon.', 66263), -- O Lonely Star
(93810, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, we need more capable arms.', 66263), -- Masters' Perch
(91149, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I felt it. When you--when he--thank you. Sorry. Getting hard to think.\n\n<She accepts the tinder box and holds it to her chest. Her eyes seem to focus on something you can\'t see.>\n\nCal...? I\'m so tired. Let\'s go home.\n\n<Anais slumps over, her hand falling away from the wound at her side. She is at peace.>', 66263), -- Bury Me Not
(91148, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had him. One spear thrust and I could have ended it... but he\'s still Cal--even with that monster controlling him.\n\n<Anais clutches at ragged cut in her side. Blood and foul Void magic flow from the wound in equal measure.>\n\nLook what chasing after him again got me.', 66263), -- Strung Along
(91146, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She\'s hurting him, throwing him into fight after fight. We don\'t have time to search this whole blasted plain.\n\nI can\'t concentrate. The Void magic here is too chaotic and volatile.', 66263), -- Flickering Light
(91147, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Removing the Shadowgrafts kills them... What good is the Light if it can\'t save one man?', 66263), -- Cut Her Strings
(91145, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Imperia\'s beasts swarmed me. I lost track of them.\n\nI shouldn\'t have left you behind, but seeing that monster control Callum... I\'m not losing him. Not while I still breathe.', 66263), -- The Conquered Heroes
(90924, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The blade, as promised. See? I never meant to keep it for myself. I will even shape it into whichever form suits you best.\n\nThe taste of your suffering was all I desired.', 66263), -- The Wicked End
(90922, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m terribly sorry you had to go through that. The words of these spirits have upset you, correct?\n\n<Decimus peers at you.>', 66263), -- The Fallen Wake
(90923, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At long last...', 66263), -- Shepherd of Fear
(90920, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating, how freely you give up delicate information about yourself.\n\nI choose to believe you would not lie to me, of course. We are friends now, you and I. Such a mortal concept intrigues me.', 66263), -- Warmth for the Soul
(90919, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Pay no mind to Vortensiun\'s comment about food. \n\nWe are becoming good friends, are we not?', 66263), -- The Fiend That Failed
(90917, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good. \n\nI understand you mortals fret over things like ecological balance and culling of species. \n\nFear not: the monsters here are as endless as they are brutal.', 66263), -- Harvester of Savagery
(90918, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, how quaint, to catch up with old enemies. \n\nWe domanaar once had intricate structures of power. Each domanaar fights for their own sake alone, but it is often advantageous to align oneself with others. Temporarily, of course. \n\nThe most powerful among us were the High Lords. When Xal\'atath arrived... she made an example of them all. The spectacle was so moving, it drew not only fear but something closer to loyalty from us domanaar. \n\nSome, though not all.', 66263), -- The Unforgiven
(90916, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These Nexus-Points used to be fonts of power for us domanaar to enjoy, long before Xal\'atath overthrew us. \n\nSomeday, they shall be so again.', 66263), -- Seek to Destroy
(91382, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is unfortunate that the beast turned out to be as pitiful and lame as you mortals.\n\nYou deserve each other.', 66263), -- Mighty and Superior
(92499, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I stand by my decision, but I should apologize both to Pel\'na and Idago.\n\nDey have wisdom to offer me... and in return, I will guide them through these troubling times.', 66263), -- The Wisest Leaders Follow
(92496, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done a great honor for our tribe by defendin\' our lands against de Twilight\'s Blade.', 66263), -- Spears Against de Shadow
(92497, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De girl\'s foolishness aside, I owe you my life.', 66263), -- Simply Magical
(92495, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By Nalorakk\'s maw, you put a dent in their forces.', 66263), -- Disruptin' de Blade
(92493, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look! There is fresh blood on his spear! Someone used de weapon recently!', 66263), -- What Remains of Idago
(92492, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stay down, $n! Don\'t give away my hidin\' spot.', 66263), -- Honorin' de Sacrifice
(91206, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What do you mean, you don\'t have de medicine? I sent you for it ages ago!\n\nWe must help him... even if de loa won\'t!', 66263), -- Loa Disturbance
(89565, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My younger brother left us when I was just comin\' of age.\n\nHe sent word he would come and help but... we did not part on good terms.\n\nBut here he is. After all dis time.', 66263), -- The Path of Mourning
(93050, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My days of combat are behind me, but I\'m glad to be helpin\' out around de village.', 66263), -- Altar History
(93096, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dis is a shameful fate for Kel\'vujo, but one dat he chose.\n\nYou, hash\'ura, have proven once again to be strong. \n\nTake dis as thanks for helpin\' to weed out de weak and unfit from our warriors.', 66263), -- Amani Honor
(93095, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! Tusk Taker is dead!\n\nDe others will see me as a true Amani warrior now--when I tell them I took all de trophies that killed Tusk Taker.', 66263), -- Bitter Fury
(93093, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat... dat is a lot of trophies there, hash\'ura.', 66263), -- Gnarldin Trophies
(93094, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dis is plenty!\n\nAll of dem were actually dead... right?', 66263), -- Scavenged Victory
(90568, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Seeker Crikkash says he wanted to wait for you to arrive before showing me what he\'s found.', 66263), -- Unlikely Friends
(90486, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I suppose now we try it. Right, $p?', 66263), -- Dangerous Delicacies
(90482, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Now to prepare it.', 66263), -- Cuisine Connection
(90485, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My my, what an interesting find!\n\nThere\'s a lot to be learned from an old pot: how the ancient Amani might have prepared food, the kinds of food they ate, and what they valued most in a meal.\n\nI\'ll work on analyzing this. You can place those other items to the side. They\'re far younger than this beauty.', 66263); -- Afterthought Artifacts
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(90483, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see. They keep clear records of all these battles at least. Their storytelling is quite strenuous!', 66263), -- A Witherbark Story
(90484, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Steggy is back! You really are response-able.', 66263), -- Sightseeing Stegadon
(90481, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He confirmed what he\'d sent was a letter of approval? Good! I\'m glad that\'s cleared up.\n\nMaybe now we can get a more pleasant introduction to Zul\'Aman.', 66263), -- I Have a Permit
(91409, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is de Shadra I remember from Shadra\'Alor. She will assist us if we help her.\n\nShe keeps her promises.', 66263), -- Dreaming of Spiders
(91630, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They must mean to weaken us and our ability to commune with Shadra.', 66263), -- Stolen Sight
(91408, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s hear him out, but keep your hand on your weapon.', 66263), -- Seeking Shadra
(91405, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De Vilebranch are de ones doin\' somethin\' with Shadra?\n\nCould de spiders be workin\' against de Witherbark? This doesn\'t make sense.', 66263), -- Validating the Venom
(91404, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, dat\'s a spider fang. Dat must have been one huge spider!', 66263), -- A Most Vile Venom
(91403, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at all de samples you found! De chief will know who can make anti-venom for sure.', 66263), -- Probable Paralytic
(93182, 1005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t know what you did or what de loa did, but I got my Kanza back and more.\n\nShe is talkin\' again like she used to. More even. She never talked a lot.\n\nAnd I\'m goin\' to make her a place where she feels safe to keep talkin\' to me.', 66263), -- Healing Homeward
(93181, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had to see her.\n\nJust one more time.', 66263), -- Temple and a Teapot
(93180, 21, 25, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, '<Kanza claps and jumps up and down excitedly.\n\nBut she pulls at your sleeve and makes an arcing motion with her hand, pointing into the far distance.\n\nThere is something else she wants you to do.>', 66263), -- Shrine Preparations
(93179, 1022, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You do not want to take the child back by force, but perhaps you can persuade her by to listen to you by helping her with what she is trying to accomplish here.\n\nJudging by the items arrayed before Filo\'s shrine, she is preparing some sort of ritual.\n\nPerhaps if you help her with the ritual, she may go with you--or go home on her own.>', 66263), -- Childlike Devotion
(93178, 1005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What was she doin\' out past de log bridge? I told her not to go there.\n\nAnd with my basket and our best tea kettle?\n\nOh... oh, no. She wouldn\'t! And alone?', 66263), -- A Quiet Walk Interrupted
(91839, 579, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All of this is my own fault. De Vilebranch so close to de village... I shoulda been more aware.\n\nMy mate leapt in de way of a death meant for me. \n\nOne moment I\'m angry, then I feel de guilt for it, and de sorrow takes\' over.\n\nAt de end of de day, I\'m keepin\' a strong face for Jin.', 66263), -- Sacrifice Denied
(91840, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah! My day\'s gettin\' better already! De Witherbark are grateful, $p.\n\nDak\'zor didn\'t say... nevermind. I don\'t wanna know.', 66263), -- One Will Not Rise
(91838, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do ya sense it? De death energy dat was oozin\' about de place feels thin.\n\nIt will take but a breath to end dis ritual for good.', 66263), -- De Vile Diminished
(91836, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In a world of horrors, we must enjoy de good we feel for causin\' dem trouble.\n\nThese pieces will go back where dey belong.\n\nYa played it well, $p.', 66263), -- Respect de Totem
(91835, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, yes, $p!\n\nIn one blow, there are more of us and less of dem!\n\nWe best make dem too afraid to ever take Witherbark again.', 66263), -- Send Dem Home
(91833, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good timing, $r! These hex masks are wicked powerful.\n\nWhatever VunVun sends our way, we will find a use.', 66263), -- Dirty Deeps
(91563, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Halazzi says he called you here to help. Is dat true, hash\'ura?', 66263), -- Halazzi's Hunt
(91407, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De spiders fled? I thought dey would put up more of a fight. And you said dey were small? Hm.\n\nWell, it doesn\'t matter. Halazzi has set us on this hunt now. We need to see it through.', 66263), -- The Eye of the Loa
(91406, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All de places dey mentioned are right next door to Shadra\'Alor! Dey probably worshipped Shadra.\n\nWe can\'t trust dem. Dey are like de venoms dey use. Dey will poison de rest of de tribe against de Revatusk--against us all!', 66263), -- Far from the Hinterlands
(93200, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re grateful for your help. Take these supplies as a gesture of thanks.', 66263), -- A Handful of Voidlight Marl
(93753, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was a close call. As for Rommath and Umbric, that\'s a puzzle for another day.', 66263), -- Magisters' Terrace
(88989, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saved de boy\'s life. And maybe now he will think before he rushes off and makes a life-endin\' decision.\n\nAnd eliminatin\' de head of de sabotage ring will allow us de time to make all de weapons we need.\n\nThings tend to work out for de best, eh? Even for you.\n\nHere\'s a little somethin\' de crew and I want you to have.', 66198), -- Another One Bites the Sawdust
(88988, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm. Not bad. For a novice.', 66198), -- The Artisan's Apprentice
(88987, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. These recovered supplies will help us return our operation to normal.\n\nDespite de elf still bein\' around...', 66198), -- Salvaged Sabotage
(88986, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De boy looks confused.\n\nGood. Maybe he\'s thinkin\'.', 66198), -- Blind the Bandits
(93929, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The tome floats in front of you. Its pages are filled with knowledge of all that has happened.>', 66192), -- The War Within Recap
(86868, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zul\'jarra has noticed your prowess in battle.\n\nGood.\n\nLet us continue demonstrating our usefulness. If they push us out of their lands now, we\'ll have no way to keep an eye on the Twilight\'s Blade until they\'re flooding through the gates into Eversong.', 66102), -- Goodwill Tour
(86711, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Many Amani found their way here, but we have more to aid.\n\nAnd even more enemies to kill.', 66102), -- Amani Clarion Call
(90749, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must say I am... surprised that Zul\'jarra allowed us passage. It has been many years since I or anyone from Eversong has stepped foot on this side of the border.\n\nStay sharp. This is a volatile situation. We may have to do more to engender their trust.\n\nBut don\'t turn your back on the Amani.', 66102), -- Our Mutual Enemy
(86710, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I find myself relieved to discover Zul\'jan is not the leader of the Amani.\n\nBut this \"Zul\'jarra\" might be worse.\n\nNo matter. We must get on the other side of that gate and assess the Twilight\'s Blade\'s threat to Eversong.', 66102), -- The Line Must be Drawn Here
(86708, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our ceasefire is strained, but holding. For now.', 66102), -- The Gates of Zul'Aman
(86650, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Would that I could join you, but there is much still to do here in Silvermoon. \n\nYou have your objectives. Keep in touch.\n\nAs for Arator... I hope you find him soon. Anu belore dela\'na, $p.', 66102), -- Fractured
(86649, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I did not expect... this. \n\n<Lor\'themar glances at Turalyon.>\n\nPerhaps we overstepped our bounds.', 66102), -- Past Redemption
(86648, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There he is--the one who leads this little incursion.', 66102), -- Light Guide Us
(86647, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must put a stop to this.', 66102), -- Beat of Blood
(86646, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is senseless. We have to stop it!', 66102), -- An Impasse
(86644, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made that look easy.', 66102), -- Gods Before Us
(86643, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Twilight\'s Blade are terrorizing Zul\'Aman as well? This is no coincidence!', 66102), -- Following the Root
(86641, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whatever their reasons, the Amani will regret this trespass.', 66102), -- Old Scars
(86642, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What have you found?', 66102), -- A Foe Unseen
(86640, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lor\'themar falls still, eyes on the shore ahead.>', 66102), -- Premonition
(86638, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve cut back what we can. I only hope it\'s enough.', 66102), -- Choking Tendrils
(86639, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Some live... I am grateful, as are they.', 66102), -- What's Left
(86637, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was not expecting reinforcements so soon! Is your business with Magister Umbric complete, then?\n\nLet\'s get moving.', 66102), -- Anything but Reprieve
(86636, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kasiea\'s notes! At long last! I must go!', 66102), -- Void Walk With Me
(86635, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am loath to find myself here again... but it is the only way.', 66102), -- To Deatholme
(86633, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No! No... I was so close.\n\n<Umbric collects himself--a paradigm of focus.>\n\nDeatholme it is, then. The base of the Twilight\'s Blade.', 66102), -- Comprehend the Void
(86634, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Twilight\'s Blade were already skulking around the perimeter... We were right to come here quickly.', 66102), -- The Past Keeps Watch
(86781, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems all is well here... for now.', 66102), -- Face the Past
(90494, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A map of Eversong? With multiple villages marked by the Twilight\'s Blade!', 66102), -- The Missing Magister
(90493, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re safe, and so are the weary citizens of Tranquillien. Thank the Light.', 66102), -- The Heart of Tranquillien
(90509, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ll need to do more to reverse the damage done here, but this was a good first step. Thank you.', 66102), -- The Traitors of Tranquillien
(86632, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I fear this is far from over...', 66102), -- The Battle for Tranquillien
(86626, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Twilight\'s Blade--Antenorian, what have you done!', 66102), -- The Ransacked Lab
(86622, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Blast--it appears that cult has ears everywhere!', 66102), -- Chance Meeting
(90907, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is heartening that you trust me with these serious concerns.', 66102), -- The First to Know
(86623, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t understand. What was she doing with all this information?', 66102), -- Appeal to the Void
(86624, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s far more to Tranquillien than meets the eye, it seems.', 66102), -- Rational Explanation
(86621, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Umbric looks stricken.>\n\nThat is not the news I was expecting. No!', 66102), -- The Wayward Magister
(86745, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hate to leave this as it stands... but Silvermoon should have enough information now to keep the Lightbloom at bay, while we wait for Orweyna\'s investigation.\n\nUntil then... we cannot address matters at the Sunwell without Umbric.', 66102), -- Silvermoon Must Know
(86744, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The rutaani are trying to spread the growth of the Lightbloom as far and wide as possible. But why?', 66102), -- Seeking Truth
(86742, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The rutaani are not like this! Not where I am from, at least. There is something affecting them. This behavior is not normal.', 66102), -- Curious Cultivation
(86743, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will bring some peace to the region for now, at least.', 66102), -- Trimming the Lightbloom
(86741, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These creatures all come from here. This Lightbloom... this is where the song of the world was leading me.', 66102), -- Lightbloom Looming
(86739, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you so much. Maybe now I can get this village back to some semblance of order!', 66102), -- Fairbreeze Favors
(86740, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This Lightbloom--it seems to be the cause of every trouble here.', 66102), -- Displaced Denizens
(86738, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A what? Giant plants? Yet another problem... at least that beast is gone for good. Thank you.', 66102), -- Sharpmaw
(86737, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness--everything is completely out of control!', 66102), -- Fair Breeze, Light Bloom
(86736, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While the Alliance and the Vanguard may become an additional stress for some, their presence is to be tolerated... for now.', 66102), -- Paved in Ash
(86734, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are those that will disagree with my decision. But I will not have us lose our home. If we must host temporary guests, so be it.', 66102), -- Diplomacy
(86733, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you\'ve arrived. Let\'s begin.', 66102), -- Silvermoon Negotiations
(86852, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May the Light bless and protect you, $n. Your defense of the Sunwell chamber made this miracle possible.\n\nWe have not beaten Xal\'atath, but we have forestalled the invasion of her Devouring Host. We now have the time to catch our breath and discover what we must do to defeat her.', 66102), -- Light's Last Stand
(86850, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the Light. Everyone from the Vanguard that survived is in the Sunwell chamber. Now that you are here, we can begin.', 66102), -- Broken Sun
(86849, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By the Light! We cannot win this battle. Our only hope lies in the Sunwell!', 66102), -- Wrath Unleashed
(86811, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. I knew I could count on you.', 66102), -- Ethereal Eradication
(86848, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Were they just here to loot us? Or did they have some reason to seek out weapons of the Light? \n\nI\'ll save that speculation for later. The Vanguard can use these weapons now. With them, we will push this Devouring Host off Quel\'Danas!', 66102), -- Light's Arsenal
(86834, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Going behind our lines was reckless! Was this Arator\'s idea? He has been so headstrong lately.\n\nSorry, $n. I shouldn\'t air this family business. I will admit that your actions have aided the Vanguard of Light in this battle.', 66102), -- Voidborn Banishing
(91274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With those void pylons destroyed, the Devouring Host has weakened. We may have a chance of winning this.', 66102), -- Severing the Void
(86807, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Champion, I am glad to hear so many of the sin\'dorei survived. Even though this was contrary to my orders to the Vanguard, you are not under my command. You acquitted yourself well. Arator did not.', 66102), -- The Gate
(86806, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The ships have crossed the strait and the refugees have made it safely to Silvermoon. Thank you, $n. You have done my people a great service.', 66102), -- Luminous Wings
(89012, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. These rescue missions are rarely as straightforward as they seem. There is always one more threat that appears that you didn\'t account for.', 66102), -- A Safe Path
(86805, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The citizens have boarded the ships. They will soon reach the safety of Silvermoon.', 66102), -- The Hour of Need
(86770, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. With this force, we can protect the survivors and escort them to the boats.', 66102), -- Champions of Quel'Danas
(86780, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. Their numbers dwindle as ours grow. The Light truly has brought hope to this battlefield.', 66102), -- Where Heroes Hold
(89271, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found him? Thank the Light!\n\nWe can\'t afford distractions. I need Arator here with the assembled forces, fully focused on the assault against Xal\'atath.', 66102), -- My Son
(86769, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must use this miraculous event to turn the tide against chaos. We must not falter.', 66102), -- Last Bastion of the Light
(88719, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Light has called you, $n. Our hope rests in the champions of Azeroth and the Vanguard of the Light!', 66102), -- A Voice from the Light
(91281, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad you came, $p. We need your help urgently.', 66102), -- Midnight
(91413, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Salhadaar cheated death to revive Dimensius, and cheated death again by escaping your wrath.\n\n<Ve\'nari pauses for a moment.>\n\nA pity he escaped, but the All-Devouring has perished. Thank you.', 66102), -- A Twilight Oath's End
(91476, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My friend! Thanks to our informants inside the Manaforge, we\'ve uncovered some technology that can help you bring it down. This translocator has been calibrated to project your soul back here for a few moments, allowing you to access whatever you may need--but be warned. The pull of Omega\'s energy fields are strong, and will rip your essence back to your body\'s position in short order. I\'m told it\'s... quite painful. Still, any advantage is a good advantage. Make haste!', 66102), -- Behind Enemy Lines
(92331, 1005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Trust thanks you for your assistance, $n. \n\nAs promised, here is your reward. \n\nTo celebrate the success of our new partnership, we are including a small performance bonus. Please return later for more work!', 66102), -- Turbo-Boost: Trade Must Flow
(93754, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Never thought I\'d feel good about saving trolls. The Witherbark better remember this act.', 66337), -- Maisara Caverns
(93766, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Together, our light will outshine the darkness the Void brings.', 66337), -- Midnight: World Quests
(91222, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It looks like your limbs are intact and there\'s nary a knife in your back. Well done, $p.', 66337), -- Prey: Phaseblade Talasha (Hard)
(94403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You make the Horde proud! Ziadan has authorized me to grant you a reward.', 66337), -- Old War Grudge
(94055, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This information shall give me the edge in the upcoming battles.', 66337), -- The Domanaar's Plan
(89354, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. As promised, here is your reward.', 66337), -- Preparing for Battle
(91249, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Please bathe before returning to the sanctum.', 66337), -- Prey: Vylenna the Defector (Hard)
(91224, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Live by the phaseblade, die by the... whatever it is you just did to them.', 66337), -- Prey: Nexus-Edge Hadim (Hard)
(90573, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your strength is matched only by your acuity, my dear. I will ensure everyone knows how marvelously you have performed today.', 66337), -- Fortify the Runestones: Magisters
(91232, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It appears you have clipped her wings. Consider me impressed.', 66337), -- Prey: The Wing of Akil'zon (Hard)
(91993, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, they are positively precious, are they not?\n\nI imagine we will see quite a few miniscule toads in handbags this coming season.', 66337), -- Diminutive Demand
(91995, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marvelous. I am certain our guests would have preferred to see the battle themselves, but tales of your heroism will do nicely.', 66337), -- What Horrible Magic
(91978, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One must appreciate the special jingle of a heavy sack of purloined coins.\n\nExcellent work, my friend.', 66337), -- Taxing the Tideborne
(89289, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent choice.\n\nI will have my valet send for them at once.', 66337), -- Favor of the Court
(93931, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Heh! So ya finally met Dundun.\n\nEven de smallest are some of de greatest among de loa!', 66337), -- An Abundance of Wealth
(94813, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your assistance. Please accept this token as thanks.', 66337), -- Fine Fashion Funding
(94671, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to you, the singularity anchor survived another assault. Take this as a sign of our appreciation.', 66337), -- Finery Funds
(93933, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n.', 66337), -- Guarded Treasures
(93932, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wonder what it is that the stones showed you. I hope you found it enlightening, $n. But remember: there is always more to learn.', 66337), -- Legendary Prosperity
(90733, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, I wanted to speak with you. \n\nThere are many truths that are hidden, even to the oldest living haranir. Continue to learn and they may be revealed.\n\nShow respect to our history, and I will eventually tell you more.', 66337), -- The Listener
(88993, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An incredible tale, worthy of preservation. I will set it into paint, ensuring it lives forever within the echoes of our people. Accept this memento--a token of my gratitude for your efforts.\n\nFor now, I will continue to go through our archives, seeking relics that cry out for understanding.\n\nReturn to me when the world has whispered more secrets to you.', 66337), -- Wey'nan's Ward
(91380, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is the beast\'s savagery growing?\n\nI\'m sure I will begin to hear of his violence from those around the Howling Ridge.', 66263), -- Belly of the Beast
(91363, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fidoficus will be renowned for his ferocity.\n\nI can see the violence growing in him.\n\nOne day, he will be a worthy pet for a domanaar such as myself.', 66263), -- Harvest of Darkness
(91545, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A violent alien world can be home, so long as it\'s got the right people.\n\nI\'ve got mine right here.', 66263), -- Stronger Than Before
(91544, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That domanaar is trying to open a portal to Silvermoon! How is this possible?', 66263), -- Familiar Energies
(91963, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are multiple styles of shadowgraft in the samples you collected. It seems like there are multiple domanaar vying for control of the power vacuum left here in Obscurion. Xal\'atath must not be in command here.\n\nWe\'ll take care of this one foe and let the rest of the domanaar fight among themselves.', 66263), -- Running Amok
(91543, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps some new class of beast will grow strong without these flying monsters to hunt them. Let\'s hope they threaten the domanaar instead of us.', 66263), -- Retaking Control
(91542, 16, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So this is where it happened.\n\nI came here simply to mourn. But... there\'s something else.', 66263), -- The Town Inside Me
(91541, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was never the best at magic, but my cantrips can at least keep tea warm.', 66263), -- Unchecked Emotions
(90915, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Consider this blade my gift to you. We shall work together to make you into a true weapon of destruction.', 66263), -- Artifice of Aggression
(90914, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My, what delightfully gruesome success. \n\nI am interested to work together with you. You should know more of our people, and see more of my abilities.', 66263), -- A Born Killer
(90847, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n! This necklace belongs to Veraan! Veraan IS Sombersong!', 66263), -- Truth From Power
(90845, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do recognize some of these items! They belonged to close friends and family.\n\nIf my sister\'s necklace is to be found, it will be here.', 66263), -- Distant Memories
(90844, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Something has sparked a rebellious fire in some of the Shadowguard.\n\nLet us see what more we can find.', 66263), -- Fits of Lucidity
(90838, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keep yourself out of sight. I would rather not risk a bleak fate.', 66263), -- Oaths and Heirlooms
(91343, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kalgorg consumed much of the Void energy within that cave, which means its influence is less likely to overwhelm my kin. I suppose some good was done.\n\nI must pay Kalgorg the slightest compliment. Were I a subdued void beast, I\'d also try to escape. For that, it has my respect.\n\n<Lucia turns to Kalgorg with a sharp smile.>', 66263), -- Ambition's Reward
(91341, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kalgorg waits before us. Now we spend the power you\'ve been collecting reclaim it.', 66263), -- Unlimited
(91339, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This too is the natural order of things.', 66263), -- Smothered in the Crib
(91340, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lucia looks you over and then rewards you with a cruel smile.>\n\nSplendid. You are as capable as you look.', 66263), -- For Violence's Sake
(90910, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kalgorg descended here, but I won\'t confront it unprepared.\n\nThat disobedient little monster. It thinks it can simply walk away after two decades?', 66263), -- Overwhelming Darkness
(91537, 16, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thought I could spare myself this pain by pushing it down.\n\nYou barely even know me. But you\'ve already done so much for me. Thank you.', 66263), -- Confronting It
(91536, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m not exactly sure how this tea is supposed to help. But I trust Hieron\'s notes.', 66263), -- Like a Weed
(91535, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve got the kettle ready.', 66263), -- Home Sweet Grave
(91887, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The creature ensnared so many of us in its web of lies.\n\nWe must remain steadfast. The Voidstorm is a terribly hostile place.', 66263), -- Dominion of Deceit
(91886, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The voidwalker\'s been feeding on us all the while... but why the misdirection? Whatever the case may be, it\'s time to end this.\n\nAnd this time, WE will have the element of surprise.', 66263), -- Voices of Omens
(91885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am better now... stable, but a fatigue still clings to me.\n\nIf we\'re to find your scouts, I will need your help.', 66263), -- Drain You
(91884, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you see them? Their cries for help... echoing... all around...', 66263), -- The Illusion of Motion
(91533, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Astre accepts Hieron\'s journal and the letter with an empty and distant expression.>', 66263), -- What We Leave Behind
(91136, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you so much, $n. You gave me a way to say goodbye to my mentor. Now that I have seen what he wanted me to, I can continue my training.\n\nIt means so much that Ja\'kul left this here for me. I miss him, but I will honor his memory.', 66263), -- Memories in Stone
(91088, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is incredible! I can\'t believe there\'s a whole cave back here. And Ja\'kul left behind a vision stone for me.', 66263), -- Behind the Falls
(91086, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is it done? Thanks. It won\'t bring Ja\'kul back, but now they won\'t be hurting anyone else.', 66263), -- Nipping the Buds
(91085, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for bringing me these feathers! I will use one of them to paint a special memorial for Ja\'kul. The rest will go to the children. \n\nI suppose it will fall to me now to teach them.', 66263), -- Petal Bristles
(91065, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! I knew they had these, those rotten weed-for-brains scavengers!\n\nI know it\'s silly to be upset about things like a favorite spoon, but they took Ja\'kul\'s life. I won\'t let them take anything else from him.\n\nYou\'re the best, $n.', 66263), -- Purloining Petals
(91063, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for coming. I wasn\'t sure you would. Up the hill that way is Blooming Lattice--a settlement of rutaani who are quite vicious.\n\nTheir leaders killed Ja\'kul, and took his things. I want them back!', 66263), -- The Blooming Lattice
(90474, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You know... I thought I would be sad if this didn\'t work, but I actually feel okay!\n\nI still believe. There\'s so much magic in the world. And even if Aln\'sharan isn\'t exactly what I think he is... his story still exists for a reason. And that\'s important to me, I think.', 66263), -- The Legend of Aln'sharan
(90470, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes! Yes, yes, yes! This is soooo much!\n\nAln\'sharan will notice for sure. He probably wants all of his skyglass back!', 66263), -- Skyglass Scavenging
(90469, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'O-Okay... so maybe I\'m a bit afraid of the dark. But that doesn\'t mean I\'m not going in there!\n\nYou\'ll be there with me too, right? There are probably tons of skyshards to be found inside!', 66263), -- Carry On, Wayward Kuri
(90467, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Goddess preserve. Kuri has always had her mind wrapped up in the roots.', 66263), -- Tales of the Sky
(90468, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kuri is as imaginative as she is fierce, but she also has a bad habit of neglecting her chores. I appreciate your contribution to our community, though I shall have to give Kuri a scolding once she returns.', 66263), -- Ugh, Chores!
(91361, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew you could do it, Riverscale! Who\'s a good grovecrawler? Who\'s the best crawler of them all?\n\nWho\'s a big strong grovecrawler who knows how to teach strangers how to care for World Trees?\n\n<Cyenna looks up at you.>\n\nYou knocked him out of his laziness, $p. I can\'t thank you enough for your help.', 66263), -- Back on Duty?
(91360, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a weed-pulling, no-rash juggernaut!', 66263), -- Weeding Out the Unwanted
(91359, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wish that I didn\'t have the laziest helper in the history of helpers, but such is life!\n\nIf his favorite treats won\'t get him up, nothing will.', 66263), -- Fungal Lashers B Gone
(91346, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This may seem inconsequential, but it\'s all a part of the process.', 66263), -- Supplicants to the Goddess
(92885, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see now that your presence here and Ketan\'s perseverance were set by the goddess herself. I am impressed by your actions and resolve. Thanks to you, Ketan\'s path is clear.', 66263), -- A Hunter's Prey
(92866, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are back, and the feeling is bittersweet. On one hand, I have lost my babies, but on the other, I know it is for the best. I could go and visit them... or maybe I shouldn\'t, considering they would be unruly and four times my size.\n\nRegardless, thank you for your help. I will never forget this kindness.', 66263), -- Re-Hydra-ted
(92865, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The budlings seem to be satiated for now. I am comfortable moving to the second phase of reintroducing them to their natural habitat.', 66263), -- Feeding the Buds
(92884, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Elder Akazi inspects the Ka\'dani spear and nods.>\n\n$n, you have proven to be a worthy mentor. Ketan deserves this weapon as much as it deserves Ketan.\n\nThe two of you have one more task before this journey comes to an end.', 66263), -- A Hunter's Weapon
(92864, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It pains me to cull the drifter population. However, if left unchecked, their numbers would have led to the collapse of the ecosystem.', 66263), -- Drift Them Away
(92883, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These look pristine.\n\nThank you for doing this for me. Maybe one day I will be able to do the same for someone else.', 66263), -- A Hunter's Duty
(90622, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, shocked! PHTeamName beat Glow Guard!\n\nI knew $p strong. But did not know if training could be enough.\n\nNot one fungarian was bet on PHTeamname. We did not think Glow Guard could be defeat. \n\nNow every fungarian know $p is best teacher of strong!', 66263), -- Not-Yet Defeated Champions
(90621, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Done teaching, now? Let\'s see what TEAMNAME can do.', 66263), -- Tiny Heroes' Journeys
(92617, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$p did not die! Ziny healed $p.\n\nWould have been Ziny\'s fault if $p died, but $p lived. Because Ziny healed, even though enemies were scary.\n\nSo scary.\n\nHooray! $p welcome. For help.\n\nAnd $p is thanked. For showing can do together.\n\nCan be Teamname now. Will win Grudge Pit, for sure.', 66263), -- Mushrooming Resilience
(92616, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sporegliders still scary. Could still sneak up and attack. Hurt Brakko\'s cap.\n\nBut $p made Brakko practice. Now can fight sporegliders, even when scared.\n\nScared does not mean Brakko have to run.\n\nReady now to fight for the Teamname.\n\nEven if we fight sporegliders, Brakko will not run.', 66263), -- Mushrooming Courage
(92618, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tuktuk could lose! Be beaten.\n\nVery scary. But $p would still be friend. Brakko would still be friend. Ziny would still be friend. \n\nWould still be the TeamName.\n\nOk, Tuktuk will try best. Will meet back at Grudge Pit.\n\nWill shoot poison again.\n\nSo much poison.\n\nEverywhere.', 66263), -- Mushrooming Confidence
(90620, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Was sure Brakko was strong enough. Was train with strong $p!\n\nBut Brakko is scared of sporegliders. Will eat cap!\n\nBrakko so sad to fail $p.\n\nZiny and Tuktuk too. All run out.\n\nWe run out, and Teamname were lose.\n\nBut how can not run out, when sporegliders attack?', 66263), -- To the Ring
(91270, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Team Name>, perfect! Now we ready.\n\nWill run into pit together, shout the <Team Name>, eh...\n\nCrowd will cheer, then will be new champions!', 66263), -- The Most Important Thing
(91450, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Already trained for the ring?\n\nWas very fast. Much impress.\n\nWhat is team\'s name?\n\nNeed name to shout when run into the Pit.\n\nAnd crowd needs name to shout when you beat other teams.\n\nOr if...', 66263), -- We Ready Now
(90619, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Eyes are open, $p! We can be strong, too.\n\nWe will be strong, like you!\n\nWhen hurt, fungarians grow stronger. You hurt lot, we grow stronger lot.\n\nMust go tell Boletus we ready!', 66263), -- What Doesn't Kill Them
(90617, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found ones to teach?\n\nFirst step is to fight, see what can do!', 66263), -- A Few Fun Guys
(90616, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We, uh... you are so strong.\n\nHow, er...? You very different.\n\nTeach fungarians, to be different like you?', 66263), -- You Strong?
(90615, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You look like could put up strong fight before start decay.\n\nWould be very interesting!', 66263), -- Be Grudge You
(92697, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve reminded me that creation isn\'t just about skill: it\'s about daring to try, imagination, and expression. Even though my work differs from the other Zur\'ashar painters, it still has worth.\n\nI need to learn to believe in myself again, and to slowly hone my craft.\n\nThank you.. for helping me see possibility where I only saw failure.\n\nI am eager, yet cautious, to begin my next piece. Perhaps this time, it will be something worthy of the name I carry.', 66263), -- Hues of Tomorrow
(92696, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Every pigment, every scrap of inspiration, will bring this idea to life, and I couldn\'t do it without you.', 66263), -- Colors Born Anew
(92695, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You actually did it? If an outsider can clean up my chaos, perhaps my work isn\'t a lost cause after all.', 66263), -- The Stroke of Storms
(92694, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you here to ridicule me as well?', 66263), -- Dusk Among Pigments
(92882, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will give you my blessing, $n. Although you are not a Ka\'dani, tales of your prowess precede you. Your skills in the hunt need no introduction.\n\nI know that you will be able to give Ketan the guidance he needs.\n\nYou will both take part in the Ka\'dani trials: you as an honorary Ka\'dani, and Ketan as your trainee.', 66263), -- A Hunter's Plight
(91410, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With Shadra aligned with us against de Vilebranch, we will punish dem grievously for their evil acts.', 66263), -- Shared Loa
(91412, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This journey has been... eye-opening. \n\nHad you asked me at the start if we would be allies with Shadra, I would have laughed in your face!', 66263), -- Return of the Venom Queen
(91411, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t imagine dat was easy. Halazzi must have blessed your hunt.', 66263), -- Maisara Caverns: Deep in Maisara
(93575, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat be a dark business indeed. So many lost, to such a terrible fate!\n\nBut no more, thanks to you. You have de Witherbark\'s gratitude... and mine.', 66263), -- Maisara Caverns: Maisara Hungers
(92061, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. That Voidstorm is evoking fear and terror in everyone who sees it, myself included. \n\nBut I chose this life of standing up to evil and spitting in its face. Sadly not everyone had the luxury of that being a choice.', 66192), -- Rising Storm
(91967, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your intercession. While I prize myself on doing what is necessary for Silvermoon and the Sunwell, I have a feeling my own patience would have worn thin and I would have said something that all of us would have regretted.', 66192), -- You Know This Evil?
(91854, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. That Voidstorm is evoking fear and terror in everyone who sees it, myself included. \n\nBut I chose this life of standing up to evil and spitting in its face. Sadly not everyone had the luxury of that being a choice.', 66192), -- Deepening Shadows
(91787, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p, for bolstering our defenders at the Sunwell.\n\nIt looks like Arator has sorted things out as well, and is ready for whatever may be ahead. It is good to have you both focused on the fight against the Void once more. \n\nArator is a good man. I\'m grateful we didn\'t lose him to this conflict.', 66192), -- The Journey Ends
(86903, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This has been a journey, $p.\n\nI\'ve learned a lot from Alonsus, and the Sons of Lothar...\n\nAnd perhaps most of all, what kind of paladin my father used to be, and what sort I\'ll be from now on.', 66192); -- The Arcantina
INSERT INTO `quest_request_items` (`ID`, `EmoteOnComplete`, `EmoteOnIncomplete`, `EmoteOnCompleteDelay`, `EmoteOnIncompleteDelay`, `CompletionText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(86894, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alndust is no mere common reagent. We must be precious about its use. For my people, though, I will not hesitate to give all I have.', 66337), -- The Gift of Aln'hara
(86892, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We do not know when the frenzy will push past the lakeshore and encroach upon our position. Better to have Rommath start the ritual sooner rather than later.', 66337), -- Survive
(86891, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Without overloading the runestones, the ritual won\'t pack enough of a punch to catch the forest ablaze. See to it, before we get pushed back even farther.', 66337), -- A Last Resort
(86890, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I only pray that they are more receptive to the truth this time around.', 66337), -- Tell the People What You Have Seen
(86887, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re short on time, $n. I can\'t execute my plan if we have Farstriders still in the field.', 66337), -- Expeditious Retreat
(90749, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', 66337), -- Our Mutual Enemy
(86885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What are you waiting for? Every moment that passes, more of those things filter through. Our odds are scant enough as it is.', 66337), -- Stem the Tides
(86884, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not delay. The longer we wait to cull this growth, the more of this forest the sin\'dorei will lose.', 66337), -- Cull and Burn
(86882, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I know that my people are ready to step up to the challenge.', 66337), -- Alndust in Right Hands
(86881, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'We need to stop the spread of the Lightbloom, lest it take over all of Harandar.', 66337), -- At the Root
(86880, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'It would be good to bring some of these items back in our hands.', 66337), -- Our Beloved, Returned
(86877, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'If these leaders are allowed to thrive, they will gather more forces to the Lightbloom. We can\'t allow that to happen.', 66337), -- Righteous Pruning
(92662, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', 66337), -- Core Collapse
(92661, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'With Telumnus dead, we\'ll be able to focus on attention on bigger threats.', 66337), -- Hammer Meet Anvil
(86867, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'We ride together!', 66337), -- Into the Lightbloom
(92660, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m sure a domanaar\'s tools will be able to stabilize a singularity.', 66337), -- Null Implements
(86866, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'This is it, $n. The moment of truth. Do we have an answer for the problems on Azeroth?', 66337), -- Can We Heal This?
(86864, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I hope that you will be able to rest here. You must know how to navigate this place.', 66337), -- Watch the Den
(86862, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'The power of the Rift of Aln is beyond mortal comprehension. What we are doing is simply borrowing some of it for a brief moment.', 66337), -- The Greater They Aln
(86861, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'These wars are a creation of my own making. They attack the larger creatures toward them by mimicking their reaction to food.', 66337), -- Herding Manifestations
(86860, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I hope that is enough.', 66337), -- Before They Grow
(86859, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Any advantage that we can have against the manifestation will give us a better chance to survive.', 66337), -- Grinding Out a Solution
(86858, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'We can save him!', 66337), -- The Madness Roots Deep
(86856, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'The process sounded simple enough--well within my abilities. But I appreciate your presence here to ground me.', 66337), -- Dampening the Call
(86855, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I did not know that these castoffs from the rift could affect us so much...', 66337), -- Consequences of Our Duty
(86851, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will let your young companion know what to do with the Alndust.', 66337), -- The Foundation of Aln
(86849, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t stop until we drive them from these shores!', 66337), -- Wrath Unleashed
(86848, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you secured our artifacts?', 66337), -- Light's Arsenal
(86844, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What artifacts have you found here, $p?', 66337), -- Light Repurposed
(86843, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you dealt with the Scarlet threat, $p?', 66337), -- Light Miswielded
(86841, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Countless great heroes are interred under the chapel, $p. \n\nHopefully their relics can be of aid to those at the Sunwell.', 66337), -- Relics of Paladins Past
(86840, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We can\'t hold back the undead forever, $p.', 66337), -- Flickering Hope
(86838, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That staff has served me and the Light for so many decades...', 66337), -- Renewal for the Weary
(86834, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We need to defeat all of the void commanders.', 66337), -- Voidborn Banishing
(86833, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for helping me with this, $p.', 66337), -- A Bulwark Remade
(86831, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you taken them out?', 66337), -- Warriors Without a Warlord
(86830, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve made a good start, $p, with Arator\'s help.', 66337), -- A True Horde of Dark Horde
(86827, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did ye get their badges, $p?', 66337), -- Due Recognition
(86826, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did ye put a stop to Nagosh?', 66337), -- Nagosh the Scarred
(86825, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you put a stop to Mar\'kag, $p?', 66337), -- Faithful Servant, Faithless Cause
(92618, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You think Tuktuk should try Grudge Pit again?', 66337), -- Mushrooming Confidence
(86824, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Got those banners dealt with, $p?', 66337), -- None Left Standing
(92617, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ziny will try to heal $p.', 66337), -- Mushrooming Resilience
(86823, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How goes the battle, $p?', 66337), -- The Dark Horde
(86822, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good trip?', 66337), -- One Final Relic
(92606, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The voice spoke true. There was something waiting here.', 66337), -- Take Up Your Gift
(92605, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These scavengers must have brought bones from all over Voidstorm.', 0), -- Honest as Bone
(86811, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you completed the mission?', 66337), -- Ethereal Eradication
(92604, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you have it? The shade won\'t be silent. It wasn\'t meant to exist like this.', 0), -- Speak in Blood
(86810, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you collected the necessary samples?', 66337), -- Harvesting the Void
(86806, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The ships full of sin\'dorei refugees are still in danger.', 66337), -- Luminous Wings
(86780, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you thwarted the enemy?', 66337), -- Where Heroes Hold
(88708, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Was any of this worth it? Did we sin\'dorei make a mistake marrying our fate to the Void?', 66337), -- Violent Conclusions
(90622, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Grudge Pit is always looking for new champions, $p. Until now, we\'ve just been finding the old ones again.', 66337), -- Not-Yet Defeated Champions
(90621, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Try again, $p? No run out!', 66337), -- Tiny Heroes' Journeys
(90619, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'We fighting you?\n\nYou are strong.\n\nFight together is good practice for be strong.', 66337), -- What Doesn't Kill Them
(90617, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Find fungarians to teach? Be strong in Pit like $p?', 66337), -- A Few Fun Guys
(90616, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Many fungarians watch the fighting.\n\nAlways so exciting!', 66337), -- You Strong?
(86745, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'We must contact Silvermoon to give them an update.', 66337), -- Silvermoon Must Know
(86744, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Ah... perhaps we have some answers.', 66337), -- Seeking Truth
(86743, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'These creatures are so odd... as if they are driven.', 66337), -- Trimming the Lightbloom
(86742, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'This makes no sense.', 66337), -- Curious Cultivation
(86740, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Perhaps we can solve this problem together.', 66337), -- Displaced Denizens
(90602, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The fungarians aren\'t always this violent and aggressive. Gomphusta must be the force driving them. He seems to be the one infecting living creatures with spores.\n\nWith him gone, the fungarians may return to a more balanced state.', 66337), -- Gomphusta
(86739, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'The sooner the village is returned to peace, the sooner I can breathe.', 66337), -- Fairbreeze Favors
(90601, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ru\'gar mentioned that the glowshrooms helped create a more robust harvest when they were mixed into the dirt he\'d planted crops in. How he even figured that out, I\'ll never know.\n\nI would like to carry on Ru\'gar\'s work. Since we\'re already here, we might as well gather what we can.', 66337), -- Gathering Glowshrooms
(86738, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Have you killed that beast yet?', 66337), -- Sharpmaw
(86736, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Have you met with everyone?', 66337), -- Paved in Ash
(86734, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'We have much to discuss.', 66337), -- Diplomacy
(86723, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I need de advise of my advisor, Torundo. And we must see why de other tribes did not heed de drums.\n\nDey may think I am desperate to ask for your help. But dey also would dare not challenge me.', 66337), -- Isolation
(88653, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'So much flesh and bone and meat. How can we resist?', 66337), -- Yolks on You
(86721, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t let de lightwood burn!', 66337), -- Everything We Worked For
(86719, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do whatever is necessary to get Kinduru to leave.\n\nHe\'s our uncle. We can\'t leave him here.', 66337), -- Important Amani
(86717, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Separate their limbs from their bodies. Tear down their banners and shelters too!', 66337), -- Show Us Your Worth
(86716, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These weapons are the difference between my people living or dying.', 66337), -- Armed by Light
(92509, 669, 669, 0, 0, 'Have you found the talon yet, $n? Without it, we cannot start Leona\'s ritual.', 66337), -- One Cruel Implement
(86715, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We cannot allow the Twilight\'s Blade to bring even more troops into Atal\'Aman.', 66337), -- Rituals Cut Short
(92508, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'With this ink, and an implement to inscribe it, Leona will be one step closer to her destiny.', 66337), -- The Mark of Sacrifice
(92506, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The energy from these spirits will serve as a conduit for us to access the past.', 66337), -- The Soul Price
(86712, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Arm my people--then we will talk again.', 66337), -- The Amani Stand Strong
(90574, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Maintaining the safety of Eversong is of utmost importance.', 66337), -- Fortify the Runestones: Blood Knights
(90573, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must ensure the runestones are charged and defended.', 66337), -- Fortify the Runestones: Magisters
(86710, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An outsider\'s view may help him see reason.', 66337), -- The Line Must be Drawn Here
(90571, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Go on. Ciphus won\'t mind.', 66337), -- The Lay of the Beast
(90569, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t bear to think of what the fungarians will do to the seeds that Ru\'gar has been carefully cultivating. He had been working with the rutaani on plants that were more hardy and produced greater yield. \n\nHis work should not be lost.', 66337), -- Back in the Bag
(92497, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just tear some pages out of de books and bring dem back here. The rest is simple.', 66337), -- Simply Magical
(92496, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'The world be better without Mish\'mosh\'s evil stainin\' it.', 66337), -- Spears Against de Shadow
(92495, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'One day, we\'re gonna march on these invaders an\' take our sedge back!', 66337), -- Disruptin' de Blade
(92493, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'d never say dis in front of my people, but I mourn Idago every day.\n\nI\'m not sure how I\'m goin\' to go on without his guidance.', 66337), -- What Remains of Idago
(90556, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'May their ilk never come around here again!', 66337), -- Cutting off the Head
(86693, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was hopin\' I would be able to rest.\n\nBut it looks like it\'s time to celebrate!', 66337), -- De Legend of de Hash'ey
(90555, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Have we found everyone yet?', 66337), -- Blessing of Freedom
(90554, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Have you destroyed the camp?', 66337), -- Leave Ashes in Your Wake
(90553, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Show them no mercy!', 66337), -- Executing the Blades
(90552, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Are you sure we don\'t need to use a little more force?', 66337), -- Interrogation
(86687, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t be afraid. If you assist dem, de loa will grant you their strength.', 66337), -- Conduit Crisis
(90549, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Have you found sign of the missing paladins?', 66337), -- Signs of the Struggle
(86686, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Every warrior healed is another sword at our side!', 66337), -- Light Indiscriminate
(90548, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'What\'d you find?', 66337), -- Twilight Missive
(86685, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And don\'t stop till dey all dead.', 66337), -- Chip and Shatter
(94409, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you here to deliver their contracts?', 0), -- Contract of Service
(86683, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where are all our warriors?', 66337), -- Hash'ey Away
(86682, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lilaju is de only person who can help us now.', 66337), -- Den of Nalorakk: Waking de Bear
(90544, 0, 1, 0, 0, '<Luma appears to be waiting for your approval.>', 66337), -- Thief at Bark
(86681, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are so few of us left. What was my brother thinking?', 66337), -- Den of Nalorakk: A Taste of Vengeance
(94403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you slain the enemy?', 66337), -- Old War Grudge
(90540, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must retrieve the rutaani before the fungarians can use them as hosts.', 66337), -- Rutaani Rescue
(90537, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quietly now. The enemy is close.', 0), -- Late Bloomers
(90535, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are continually making ourselves new, even as we hold to what came before. I should remember this more often.', 66337), -- Leave Your Mark
(90533, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Never try to take something from a beast like this without offering something better. \n\nI would hate to lose another friend that way.', 66337), -- Go Get Orweyna!
(86665, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Let\'s get dis over with.', 66337), -- Face in the Fire
(86663, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'This loa speaker\'s holding onto his faith a bit like Kinduru. But Kinduru knows how to speak clearly what he means. Usually.', 66337), -- Embers to a Flame
(86661, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'We have come dis far. We must try to resurrect de dead loa.', 66337), -- Coals of a Dead Loa
(92453, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Jumpin\' off dat waterfall isn\'t so scary anymore.', 66337), -- Fearless
(86655, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I hope we are doing dis right.', 66337), -- De Ancient Path
(86654, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'The gnarldin seem ready to fight us. Let\'s give them what they want, shall we?', 66337), -- Gnarldin Bashing
(86652, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Ancestors willing, we will find our opportunity to strike back soon.', 66337), -- Left in the Shadows
(86650, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is much to do.', 66337), -- Fractured
(90509, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We cannot allow these traitors to escape!', 66337), -- The Traitors of Tranquillien
(86644, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s a way out of here--I know it.', 66337), -- Gods Before Us
(86643, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'There must be a reasonable answer for all of this.', 66337), -- Following the Root
(86639, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'By the Light... this is so much worse than I would have ever imagined.', 66337), -- What's Left
(94361, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Temperance, acolyte.\n\nThere is still more abundance to be collected yet.', 66337), -- The Abundant Life
(86636, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s be done with this. The Twilight\'s Blade must fall.', 66337), -- Void Walk With Me
(86635, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Watch your back. The ruins of Deatholme are still dangerous.', 66337), -- To Deatholme
(86634, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s odd being here. This place is... well, I suppose it\'s technically my namesake.', 66337), -- The Past Keeps Watch
(86633, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t hold this indefinitely--a little speed would be appreciated!', 66337), -- Comprehend the Void
(90494, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will not allow them to get away with this.', 0), -- The Missing Magister
(86624, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How goes your investigation?', 66337), -- Rational Explanation
(90486, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'What do you think this is going to taste like? Amaxi says it\'s absolutely arresting and could kill a stegodon!', 66337), -- Dangerous Delicacies
(86623, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Was she on to a breakthrough? Let\'s find out.', 66337), -- Appeal to the Void
(90485, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Found anything exciting yet?', 66337), -- Afterthought Artifacts
(86622, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s get to the bottom of this.', 0), -- Chance Meeting
(90484, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Have you seen how big the trolls are? Steggy is going to be bigger than the trolls, but she\'s still little like me.\n\nSteggy needs to eat so she can get bigger. Please find her so I can feed her!', 66337), -- Sightseeing Stegadon
(86621, 989, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s that you have there?', 0), -- The Wayward Magister
(90483, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'What\'s wrong with a gentle story about falling asleep at an inopportune time?\n\nTortollan folklore is full of those. Do trolls not sleep?', 66337), -- A Witherbark Story
(90482, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'We ingest some poisons to make ourselves resistant to potential threats.\n\nSome just taste good or provide a good thrill.', 66337), -- Cuisine Connection
(90481, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Elder Ren\'zen seemed so pleasant in his letters. Why all the hostility now?', 66337), -- I Have a Permit
(92407, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you removed the anomalies?', 66337), -- Hidey-Hole
(90474, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Come on! We don\'t wanna miss our chance! Also all of this skyglass is heavy. Can\'t you carry some?!', 66337), -- The Legend of Aln'sharan
(90470, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Come onnn! We\'ve gotta hurry before mom gets TOO worried.', 66337), -- Skyglass Scavenging
(90468, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, Kuri...', 0), -- Ugh, Chores!
(90467, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aln\'sharan is a folk tale that we tell haranir children to explain the shards of glass that occasionally rain upon Harandar.\n\nMost grow out of searching for sky serpents. But Kuri\'s heart has always been filled with whimsy.', 0), -- Tales of the Sky
(92397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you finished setting up?', 66337), -- Dawnstar Defense
(92365, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you deployed the defenses?', 0), -- Creating Defenses
(86562, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you found the greatest of the enemies here? I wonder just how powerful a creature can get, consuming Void for eternity...', 66337), -- Dancing with Death
(86561, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The metal on these creatures... it seems particularly conductive to magical energies. Interesting.', 66337), -- A Strange, Different World
(86558, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Be careful, $c. Treachery threatens us from all sides.', 66337), -- Save a Piece of Mind
(86545, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I should have realized earlier... Join me, $n. Let us reveal the truth.', 66337), -- The Light's Brand
(86544, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mother... Hang in there.', 66337), -- Post-Mortem
(86541, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Decimus glances sideways at you.>', 0), -- Just In Case...
(92332, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Again, you prove yourself a friend of the cartels! Well done.', 66337), -- Turbo-Boost: Infinite Growth
(86538, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Go. Collect the catalyst.', 66337), -- Second, The Fuel
(86537, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What have you found?', 66337), -- Network Insecurity
(86536, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lothraxion has a plan. I trust him.', 66337), -- Reliable Enemies
(86530, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just as before.', 0), -- First, The Shells
(86521, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'We\'ve come too far to let anything stop us.', 66337), -- Nexus-Point Xenas: Eclipse
(86517, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Lothraxion should know better than this.', 66337), -- Vanished in the Void
(86516, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'These creatures operate on base instinct. We can exploit that.', 66337), -- All Become Prey
(86515, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Would that we could put every voidspawn to the sword.', 66337), -- Hollow Hunger
(86514, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you claimed Torentia\'s sigil?', 0), -- Lady of the Pit
(86513, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Even if we fail--Light forfend--at least we\'ll have struck a blow.', 66337), -- Face the Tide
(86512, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Do you feel the hunger of this place? No wonder the Void came here.', 66337), -- The Harvest
(86511, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I\'ve avoided this place until now. The howls and the stench are carried on the wind like a warning.', 66337), -- Edge of the Abyss
(92177, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who would have known this power was here all along, ripe for the taking?', 66337), -- One Hero's Prey
(92167, 0, 14, 0, 0, 'The Deepfin must be banished from these lands!', 66337), -- There Can Be Only One
(92166, 0, 25, 0, 0, '$n! I command you to return my priestess unharmed.', 66337), -- Following Suit
(92165, 25, 25, 0, 0, 'My kingdom is ready for a feast! Are you prepared?', 66337), -- Fish Are Food, Not Friends
(92164, 0, 273, 0, 0, 'I await your victorious return!', 66337), -- Murloc Madness
(92159, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She did not give you mercy. Don\'t give her any either.', 66337), -- A Final Destination
(92157, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ll destroy the hiding places, and draw it out.', 66337), -- Ritual Activity
(92156, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Defeated duelists should be perfect. Mark them with the brand.', 66337), -- It Follows Me
(92155, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Be cautious as you check this area. We don\'t know what we\'re dealing with, yet.', 66337), -- Object Exorcism
(94057, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you obtained my gift?', 0), -- A Golden Pull
(94055, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you obtained the battle plans?', 66337), -- The Domanaar's Plan
(92084, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'My vision is clearing, and so is my mind.', 66337), -- Halazzi's Guile
(94012, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Ya find her?', 66337), -- Lost Lil' Strider
(93997, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you seized control of each of the Void Posts?', 66337), -- Void Post Control
(92061, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tensions are high.', 66337), -- Rising Storm
(93970, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Please do not drop the sample.', 66337), -- Researching the Storm
(93965, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'What sort of friend will you bring back, I wonder?', 66337), -- Pet Wranglin'
(92025, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Time is of the essence. Talandra\'s ritual approaches.>', 66337), -- Flowers for Amalthea
(92023, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Eugh. Why do I smell grave soil on you?', 66337), -- Suspicious Sundries
(92022, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Strictly speaking, a stronger venom would have a more ample effect. But we\'re living in strenuous times. This Void hooplah has my usual supply lines at Sunsail completely occupied. We\'ll have to make do with mournbat venom. Now go.', 66337), -- A Venomous Vocation
(92021, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, come now. While we stand here and chat about the weather, my associate continues to suffer under the travails of her malady! Get on with it.\n\nIt\'s gloomy, by the way. The weather. As usual.', 66337), -- Graveblossom Gardening
(92010, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Try to take Slewstalk down before she can get those long grippers of hers around you.', 66337), -- WANTED: Slewstalk's Stalks
(93933, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'Have you defended the anchor from the encroaching void forces?', 66337), -- Guarded Treasures
(93932, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'What have you uncovered, $n?', 66337), -- Legendary Prosperity
(93931, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'Did you find de loa, hash\'ura?', 66337), -- An Abundance of Wealth
(93930, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'So, how\'s the party going? Do you need any etiquette tips?', 66337), -- Courting Success
(91995, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust this task is within your skill set.', 66337), -- What Horrible Magic
(91993, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fear not. The enchantment is quite permanent.', 66337), -- Diminutive Demand
(91980, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hurry up and put Hellebora down before she wanders out of the mire.', 66337), -- WANTED: Hellebora's Thorn
(91979, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'Is the issue resolved?', 66337), -- Chop It Down
(91978, 6, 6, 0, 0, 'Is it still stealing when stolen from thieves?', 66337), -- Taxing the Tideborne
(91974, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'How did it go?', 66337), -- Sunfire to the Blade
(91972, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'How was Bloodguard Nelric?', 66337), -- Hold the Watch
(91970, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What are you talking to me for, when you should be out there killing Gelatonius?', 66337), -- WANTED: Gelatonius
(91967, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Umbric is necessary. So is the Vanguard. \n\nI have a lot of necessary and unsavory elements to deal with these days, but I will do so if it means my people are safe.', 66337), -- You Know This Evil?
(91963, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you gathered enough for us to study?', 66337), -- Running Amok
(91958, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De final trial is at hand.', 66337), -- Den of Nalorakk: Unforgiven
(93889, 0, 1005, 0, 0, 'Tread carefully, $n. The Silvermoon Court is as much a battlefield of words as it is of deeds. Do not let yourself be chewed up by its ever-turning gears.', 66337), -- Midnight: Saltheril's Soiree
(93865, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Go. Show me a bout.', 66337), -- Carve Your Way
(91933, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are few things amongst mortals or gods that cannot be viewed through the lens of trade.\n\nSome of us are simply... less coy about that truth than others are.', 66337), -- The Abundant Honor
(91932, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not fear. I am indeed the finest judge of your every action and choice.', 66337), -- The Abundant Awakening
(91929, 0, 15, 0, 0, 'Is that mercenary well fed?', 0), -- What's For Lunch?
(93850, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Please... help us.', 66337), -- Windrunner Spire: Haunting Melodies
(91875, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you have the rejuvenating mud I asked for?', 0), -- Natural Remedy
(93801, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This place has such vitality. It\'s no wonder the pathogen has spread so easily.', 66337), -- Calculated Culling
(91854, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tensions are high.', 66337), -- Deepening Shadows
(91842, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Get those taken care of, $p?', 66337), -- Disarm the Dark Horde
