(91747, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t want them. We\'ll toss them on the fire.', 66337), -- Not Quite Nalorakk
(91726, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It was such a dark day, $p. Painful to remember.', 66337), -- Unstoppable Force
(91700, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you eliminated the threats?', 66337), -- Darkness Unmade
(91693, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do endeavor not to keep our guests waiting in suspense.', 66337), -- The Subtle Game
(93575, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gather your warparty. I will see you in Maisara Caverns.', 66337), -- Maisara Caverns: Maisara Hungers
(91630, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can understand why dey want de venom, but de artifacts are just for communin\' with Shadra. What would dey need with them?', 66337), -- Stolen Sight
(91629, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Pick any invitation you desire.', 66337), -- High Esteem
(91628, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your presence is already turning heads. This will be quite the spectacle.', 66337), -- Honored Guests
(91606, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is the grafter dead?', 66337), -- Voidscar Arena: Clearing House
(91589, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Once the meal is set, our job will be done for today.', 66337), -- Root Dash Delivery
(91588, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'How is the preparation coming along?', 66337), -- Harandar's Kitchen
(91587, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Did you bring the rind?', 66337), -- Carcass Cuisine
(91586, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'I hope you bring news of good soil.', 66337), -- Soil-Based Alternatives
(91585, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'I hope you brought back a good harvest.', 66337), -- Fresh from the Garden
(91561, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Have you contained the spread of this deadly pathogen?', 66337), -- Bloodborne Pathogen
(47148, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even I could not foresee the strange ways in which you would fight your enemies $n.', 66337), -- Something Different
(91560, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Were you successful? Did the antidote work?', 66337), -- Expunging Explorers
(91559, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How goes the hunt? Have you gathered what we need?', 0), -- Virulent Vermin
(91558, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you collect enough yet?', 0), -- Pestilent Petals
(91556, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not long now, Tolbani.', 66337), -- Loa's Flame
(91546, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'At least I\'m not visiting my parents.', 66337), -- To Be Changed
(91543, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have they been dealt with?', 66337), -- Retaking Control
(91537, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Astre holds their forehead.>', 66337), -- Confronting It
(91536, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Astre thumbs through Hieron\'s journal with a detached expression.>', 66337); -- Like a Weed
INSERT INTO `quest_request_items` (`ID`, `EmoteOnComplete`, `EmoteOnIncomplete`, `EmoteOnCompleteDelay`, `EmoteOnIncompleteDelay`, `CompletionText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(91535, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Astre thumbs through Hieron\'s journal with a detached expression.>', 66337), -- Home Sweet Grave
(87672, 0, 273, 0, 0, 'The Voidstorm threatens our very existence. We cannot stay long.', 66337), -- Void is in the Air
(91533, 6, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve recovered some since we last parted ways here, but the whispers continue to plague me. They\'re insidious, torturing me with what I lack, how I\'ve failed. And--\n\nWait. Is that...? Where did you get that?', 0), -- What We Leave Behind
(93437, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are grateful Akil\'zon opened our eyes to de truth of Zul\'jin and Malacrass\'s dark deeds.\n\nEven if it means we accept their shame as our own.', 66337), -- In Their Own Blood
(91505, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'We can\'t let the naga get any closer to Goldenmist.', 66337), -- Daggers in My Spine
(93436, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us prove dat even echoes of de past can feel woe.', 66337), -- Hex the Innocent, Disrupt the Guilty
(93435, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can ya believe de instigators even returned years later when de Zandalari propped their puppet leader up?\n\n\"Immortal,\" my rear...', 66337), -- Four Instigators
(93433, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s their status? Any issues with de barriers?', 66337), -- Shrine, Sealed, Delivered
(93432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s like a dream you can\'t wake from.', 66337), -- Swords to Plowshares
(91495, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'The Farstriders are grateful for your assistance.', 66337), -- Familiar Faces in Peril
(93426, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s more to look out for.', 0), -- Sparks of War: Voidstorm
(91494, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Maybe the wand was too weak for its original owner. Whatever the case, we can try to put it to good use.', 66337), -- One Elf's Trash, Another Elf's Treasure
(91493, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'The blood elves could just use magic to trade. But there\'s something dependable about a sturdy wooden box.\n\n<Hathvelion thumps the table beside him and smiles.>\n\nPlus, I hear food and drink aren\'t as tasty after being transported by magic.', 66337), -- Not What I Ordered
(89560, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s time. We are ready.', 66337), -- A Quiet Farewell
(89559, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We both know dat de shrine is a place dat pleased our mother.\n\nI can\'t say she knew dat much about us.', 66337), -- Reasonless Worship
(93421, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'How fighting?', 66337), -- Delver's Call: The Grudge Pit
(93396, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'She may not be completely herself, but she seems to be resisting the worst of it.', 66337), -- Bursting at the Seams
(91452, 989, 989, 0, 0, 'It really takes everyone to get through times like these.', 66337), -- Range of Knowledge
(89513, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not worry for Kan\'sha. She has outlived generations of trolls, and de druids say she\'ll survive many more.', 66337), -- Kindling Aplenty
(93372, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'Yes, $n?', 66337), -- Delver's Call: Shadow Enclave
(89507, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', 66337), -- Abundant Offerings
(89506, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De sinew of mountain giants is a strong buildin\' material.\n\nBut we only use it for dis one purpose, because it\'s dangerous to get and there are not enough giants.', 66337), -- Strong Ties
(89503, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re called weepin\' spores, because when dey burn dey make your eyes water.\n\nDe spores give our warriors a good excuse if dey are too cowardly to admit their feelings at de pyre.', 66337), -- Somber Siblings
(95276, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'There\'s plenty out there that can be done.', 66337), -- The Last Push
(91412, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is more than de return of a loa--it is a bridge between tribes.', 66337), -- Return of the Venom Queen
(91411, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think dat Shadra will honor her word.', 66337), -- Maisara Caverns: Deep in Maisara
(91409, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De two artifacts should be enough to speak to a vision of Shadra.', 66337), -- Dreaming of Spiders
(91408, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where dis trail leads, we follow.', 66337), -- Seeking Shadra
(91407, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did Halazzi help you? He can hear anything, but he also can see what\'s hidden in shadow.', 66337), -- The Eye of the Loa
(91406, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dey probably brought their worship of Shadra with dem.', 66337), -- Far from the Hinterlands
(91404, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you look for de big fang?', 66337), -- A Most Vile Venom
(91403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Halazzi says venomous is when dey bite or stab you, and poisonous is when you bite or eat dem! Isn\'t dat interestin\'?', 66337), -- Probable Paralytic
(91402, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If dey start bringing the void here we\'re gonna be in a whole heap o\' trouble.', 66337), -- Ultra Deadly Ultradon
(91401, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why femurs? None of ya business.', 66337), -- Dead by Dusk
(91400, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look for de sharpest axes. Those be ours.', 66337), -- Blades of the Fallen
(91399, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t worry, we been doin\' dese rituals for centuries.', 66337), -- Ashes of the Void
(91398, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Get me de tomes.', 66337), -- Tomes of Terror
(91388, 989, 989, 0, 0, 'This is the easy part, of course.', 66337), -- Uncommon Threads
(91386, 0, 989, 0, 0, 'If only a single soul among these brutes showed any appreciation... alas, it seems even this small ask is too great.', 66337), -- Mad to Measure
(91385, 0, 989, 0, 0, 'The beauty of the forest? It never gets old.', 66337), -- A Ranger's Spirit
(91384, 989, 989, 0, 0, 'If we want to be of any use to the rest of Eversong, first we must pick up after ourselves.', 66337), -- Recovery Mission
(95245, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The defense of our city is ceaseless work.', 66337), -- Midnight: World Tour
(91382, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Fidoficus has grown fearsome, and perhaps you have claim to some of his growth.', 66337), -- Mighty and Superior
(91381, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To have this wide of an affected area... It should never have been this hard to find.\n\nBe wary. If this thing is truly trying to protect itself, then its most dangerous hosts will be close at hand.', 66337), -- Reticent Evil
(91379, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is no evil afoot here. It\'s simpler than that. Whatever this is wants to live, and these dead fungarians are a means for it to do so.\n\nBut it cannot be allowed to persist. Even if it is natural, it remains unacceptably dangerous.', 66337), -- Decayed Land
(91378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not feel regret. These things are not alive anymore. Not in any way that matters.', 66337), -- You Are Legend
(91377, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot shake the feeling that something is terribly wrong here.', 66337), -- Spawn of the Dead
(91376, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do not know what is going on, but to err on the side of caution... do not let them bite you, hrm? Whatever plagues them may be infectious.', 66337), -- Little Monsters
(91363, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'These ingredients will make for a highly nutritious and equally delectable meal.', 66337), -- Harvest of Darkness
(91361, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Please tell me that worked. I\'m just about out of ideas.', 66337), -- Back on Duty?
(91360, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I look forward to this job the least. You\'re doing me a huge favor.', 66337), -- Weeding Out the Unwanted
(91359, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'It\'s important that we keep the lashers from sapping important nutrients from the World Tree.\n\n...and I like spoiling my obstinate little boy.', 66337), -- Fungal Lashers B Gone
(91349, 989, 989, 0, 0, 'It\'s hard work, but it will bring peace eventually.', 66337), -- The Dark Part of the Woods
(91348, 989, 989, 0, 0, 'Don\'t worry! They bounce right back.', 66337), -- See a Mana 'bout a Wyrm
(91347, 989, 989, 0, 0, 'Nothing like planting seeds.', 66337), -- Strider Stampede
(91346, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'The water washes away the outside.', 66337), -- Supplicants to the Goddess
(91341, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'The trail of carnage it left behind... I\'m almost proud.', 66337), -- Unlimited
(91340, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Slaughter them. It is our way.', 66337), -- For Violence's Sake
(91339, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t fear power, $n: fear those who wield it.', 66337), -- Smothered in the Crib
(93261, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'I don\'t know if de Twilight\'s Blade created dat beast or not, but it needs to GO!', 66337), -- A Crab of Unusual Size
(93260, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Were you able to clean any of de traps? Or find a source of de filth gumming them up?', 66337), -- Caging Crawlers
(91328, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you gathering carefully?', 66337), -- Secret Ingredients
(93259, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'My people have been through so much. Everyone deserves a warm home to return to, and a hearty meal to restore their strength and spirit.', 66337), -- Clobbering Crawlers
(93258, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I must make dis right--for my people. For my mother. I wish she could give us guidance.', 66337), -- Crab Clues
(87457, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'This necklace was in a camp we cleared of demons. Must\'ve been for a ritual, but we stopped them from cursing it.', 66337), -- What We Do Best
(87456, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Have you found all the souvenirs? We got other things for the rest of our crew back in Suramar, but we didn\'t have time to mail these when we escaped.', 66337), -- Souvenirs Scattered
(89386, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you find the golden sunleaf?', 66337), -- A Roost-ed Development
(89384, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you found any frogs? The hawkstriders are hungry!', 66337), -- A Hungry Flock
(89383, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you find the hatchling?', 66337), -- One Adventurous Hatchling
(29518, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Did you manage to find any scrap? The grounds are full of it.', 66337), -- Rearm, Reuse, Recycle
(29511, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'You get those repairs done? Visitors are hard on those tonks and I\'ll need all of them up and running.', 66337), -- Talkin' Tonks
(91301, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you have any business with the academy?', 66337), -- How to Train Your Protege
(91292, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well? Is the staff charged, or are you wasting both our lives?', 66337), -- A Test of the Arcane
(91291, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, what do you think?', 66337), -- A Test of Blood
(91288, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you gotten those pelts yet or are you quitting already?', 66337), -- A Test of the Hunt
(89354, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This isn\'t enough! Go clear more of the void creatures.', 66337), -- Preparing for Battle
(91284, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I really hope I find where I belong...', 0), -- A Path Not Yet Chosen
(91271, 6, 6, 0, 0, 'Have you hooked the one?', 66337), -- A Fish!
(91270, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Find best name?', 66337), -- The Most Important Thing
(89338, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'The weapons we gather will help reforge Hammerfall\'s future, $p.', 66337), -- Gathering Plowshares
(89334, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Take their heads. How painful de method is between you and whatever force you worship.', 66337), -- Ahead of the Issue
(87402, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We cannot wait.', 66337), -- The Light Provides
(87401, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes?', 66337), -- Gardener Mishap
(87399, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'How goes the hunt?', 66337), -- Facing the Sun
(87397, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I trust you gave that cargo a proper send-off.', 66337), -- Cargo Collateral
(87396, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Get after them!', 66337), -- Dead to Rights
(87395, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'So what did our friends at Tideborne Freight so desperately want to hide? Their scuttling cannot conceal their true intentions forever.', 0), -- Below the Brine
(87394, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'You\'re back, and with the recordings, I hope.', 66337), -- Supplier Surveillance
(87393, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Back already? Let\'s hear it. What did you uncover about the Tideborne? And don\'t leave out any details', 66337), -- Warranted Search
(87392, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'So, what did our fine dockworkers have to say?', 66337), -- Cargo Conspiracy
(87391, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Can there even BE a ruler of such a chaotic animal kingdom?', 66337), -- Sampling the Local Fare
(93181, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kanza looks nervous and expectant.>', 66337), -- Temple and a Teapot
(87388, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'There is a connection between these beasts and the Void... not so unlike the ren\'dorei.', 66337), -- A Bigger Beast
(93180, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kanza shifts her weight from foot to foot, swaying impatiently.>', 66337), -- Shrine Preparations
(93179, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kanza eyes you uncertainly.>', 66337), -- Childlike Devotion
(93178, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m so worried about Kanza!\n\nShe shouldn\'t be on her own.', 66337), -- A Quiet Walk Interrupted
(89289, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Be cautious, as always. The sin\'dorei take great offense to many subtle things.', 66337), -- Favor of the Court
(29417, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'To not act is to abandon reason.', 66337), -- The Way of the Huojin
(89276, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Time is of the essence, dear.', 66337), -- Light Snacks
(89271, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you found my son?', 66337), -- My Son
(91197, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The domanaar need void-tainted remains to fuel their war effort. Scavenge the area or slay fellow adventurers across Slayer\'s Rise to obtain this resource.', 0), -- Collecting Remains
(87317, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why aren\'t ya helpin me?!', 66337), -- Denial Denied
(89233, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Dey are both good choices...', 66337), -- Love Triangle
(93095, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'Did you kill Tusk Taker yet?', 66337), -- Bitter Fury
(93094, 6, 6, 0, 0, 'With those tablets, no one can question our strength!', 66337), -- Scavenged Victory
(89231, 6, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you need somethin\'?', 0), -- A Fighter Not a Lover
(93093, 6, 6, 0, 0, 'Did you get de trophies? De gnarldin have plenty of dem from all their fightin\'.', 66337), -- Gnarldin Trophies
(89230, 6, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you need somethin\'?', 0), -- A Lover Not a Fighter
(91149, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My parents always said falling in love with a human would end in heartbreak.\n\n<She doesn\'t lift her head.>\n\nThere\'s never enough time, is there?', 0), -- Bury Me Not
(89208, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you recruited our dear assassin to the cause. Well done.', 66337), -- What We're Owed
(89206, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re getting them out of here.', 66337), -- Break and Enter
(91137, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'Did they make it back?', 66337), -- Lost in Light
(89205, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That staff should be able to break this ward now.', 0), -- Cutting a Key
(89204, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the easy part.', 0), -- Five Finger Discount
(89203, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Come on. Spit out the details.', 66337), -- Mutual Benefit
(89201, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will be taking those documents back.', 0), -- Outschemed
(89199, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do handle the wardbreaker carefully. I will not tolerate seeing it damaged.', 66337), -- A Small Task
(87268, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Show dem de staff. See what dey remember.', 66337), -- Required Repentance
(87267, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kulzi cannot keep ignorin\' us!', 66337), -- Demands Unmet
(93051, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not pull even a single punch. De boy must succeed or fail on his own.\n\nIf he\'s not ready, you will be doin\' him no favors sendin\' him into the fray unprepared.', 66337), -- The Final Exam
(93050, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I just need to take a little breather here.\n\nDon\'t go worryin\' about me, now. Keep focused on the task at hand, eh?', 66337), -- Altar History
(93049, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you get all of dem?', 66337), -- Homework Support
(87256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dey must be pungent if dey gonna work.', 66337), -- Alternative Medicine
(93048, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Makin\' progress, yah?', 66337), -- Got No Rhythm
(93047, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De art of Amani huntin\' is about discipline. You practice until de skills come as naturally as breathin\'.\n\nBut right now, discipline means doin\' what I tell you.', 66337), -- Butchery Basics
(87254, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Make sure it is large enough.', 66337), -- Curse Cleanse
(93043, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Speak with Astalor Bloodsworn to continue.', 66337), -- When Predator Becomes Prey
(91090, 0, 6, 0, 0, 'Are the insects giving you trouble?', 66337), -- Pesky Pests
(91086, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The rutaani are not usually this violent. Ja\'kul used to say that he thought this lot is because they built their village too close to the fungarians of Fungal Cleft.\n\nHave you dealt with those bud-heads yet?', 66337), -- Nipping the Buds
(91085, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you gathered the petalwing plumes I asked for? They\'re essential for the lessons of the younger haranir.', 66337), -- Petal Bristles
(91071, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De river\'s dangerous. We must reclaim it.', 66337), -- The Menace of Atal'Abasi
(91070, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, $c?', 66337), -- Reclaim the Goods
(91069, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bleed de mindless beasts. Make dem suffer for killin\' Tolbani.', 66337), -- Vengeance for Tolbani
(91065, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those birds would steal your head if it wasn\'t attached to your shoulders. Especially if you were wearing a shiny hat or helm. Right off your shoulders!\n\n<She pauses for a moment as if picturing this, then turns slightly green and shudders.>', 66337), -- Purloining Petals
(92948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sensed no remorse at all from him. How could that be?', 66337), -- In Over My Head
(92946, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What more could we learn?', 66337), -- Buried in the Dark
(92945, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Speak with Astalor Bloodsworn to continue.', 66337), -- The Power of Anguish
(92944, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had some suspicion about these runes not being domanaar or ethereal. The specter all but confirms my thoughts. This could be something different. Maybe even a civilization!', 66337), -- Sifting Through Void
(92939, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why are these beasts even eating these rocks?', 66337), -- It's Not Just a Rock!
(91000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is much to do, $p.', 66337), -- A Humble Servant
(94849, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You remain alive. Does your target?', 66337), -- Voidscar Arena: A Familiar Grudge
(94848, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you possess what it takes to survive in these lands, $rs?', 66337), -- Voidscar Arena: Pre-Provoked Violence
(94845, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What trickery have you found?', 0), -- Voidscar Arena: The Bastion of Might
(94835, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have yet to finish your training for the week.', 66337), -- Early Morning Training: Week 1 of 4
(89034, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Lightbloom cannot be allowed to spread. The harmony of Har\'mara is delicately balanced. We must keep it intact.', 66337), -- Burning Bitterblooms
(92885, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Is the task done?', 66337), -- A Hunter's Prey
(92884, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Forging a Ka\'dani weapon is not an easy feat. A master craftsman must use the very best materials brought by the mentor and trainee.', 66337), -- A Hunter's Weapon
(92883, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'Were you able to get everything? I know some of the required materials can be hard to gather.', 0), -- A Hunter's Duty
(92882, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Ketan tells me that you wish to mentor him. Is this true?', 66337), -- A Hunter's Plight
(89012, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Does the engulfing Void still bar the way?', 66337), -- A Safe Path
(92869, 0, 1022, 0, 0, 'Hurry! They\'re terribly delicate creatures!', 66337), -- Fishy Dis-pondencies
(92866, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'How are my budlings doing? Precious babies that they are.', 66337), -- Re-Hydra-ted
(92865, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'The precious budlings will be very happy with their first taste of the chloroceros buds.', 66337), -- Feeding the Buds
(92864, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'How goes the task? Any success?', 66337), -- Drift Them Away
(94790, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Back so soon?', 66337), -- Research Console: Exploring the Void
(88994, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Has your journey revealed the truth of the Cauldron of Echoes? Share what you have uncovered.', 66337), -- The Cauldron of Echoes
(90924, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your patience has been... appreciated.', 66337), -- The Wicked End
(88993, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Has your journey revealed the truth of Wey\'nan\'s Ward? Share what you have uncovered.', 66337), -- Wey'nan's Ward
(90923, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t get distracted, now. This will all be worth it when you have a mighty weapon to hold.', 66337), -- Shepherd of Fear
(90922, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Such a strange and terrible place. Fear not--if you wish to converse more to settle your nerves... I am here for you.', 66337), -- The Fallen Wake
(88989, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat commander killed some of our own.\n\nHis troops most likely killed de boy\'s sister.\n\nBut even though killin\' him would make craftin\' weapons and sendin\' dem back to Amani\'Zar easier, it\'s not worth dat boy\'s life.', 66337), -- Another One Bites the Sawdust
(90920, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We domanaar occasionally will exchange witticisms. To spar with one\'s intellect is simply another form of violence--a form that few other creatures in Voidstorm have mastered. It has its merits. \n\nTo have a conversation in which there is an emotional exchange... I can\'t say I understand it, but I am eager to learn.', 66337), -- Warmth for the Soul
(88988, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De lightwood is challengin\' to work with, even for experienced woodcrafters.\n\nBe patient. Be precise. And do everything I say.', 66337), -- The Artisan's Apprentice
(88987, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'De chaos de elf caused is nothin\' next to what we\'re facin\' every day.\n\nWe have to be extra cautious with de Twilight\'s Blade tryin\' to sabotage our every move.', 66337), -- Salvaged Sabotage
(90918, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Noxian, Averus, and Tenebre... all lackeys of Xal\'atath, just like the majority of my kin. I wonder how long each would wait before attempting their betrayal of her.\n\nShame we\'ll never get to see their attempts.', 66337), -- The Unforgiven
(88986, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat boy came here seekin\' revenge on de first trolls he saw.\n\nKeep his restraints tight. Dat should help him sober up to de consequences of his childish recklessness.', 66337), -- Blind the Bandits
(90917, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The monsters native to this land are fierce and violent. Their bloodlust drew the Void here, so naturally... we feel quite at home here.', 66337), -- Harvester of Savagery
(90915, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How excellent to spend some time together. You mortals are so very interesting... you most of all.', 0), -- Artifice of Aggression
(90914, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What an odd feeling. I feel almost... drawn to you. It must be your mesmerizing presence.', 66337), -- A Born Killer
(88979, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you manage to retrieve the journal?', 0), -- Caught Red-Handed
(90910, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Disobedient little...', 66337), -- Overwhelming Darkness
(88978, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'What do you mean none of them had the journal? How is this even possible?\n\nIt defies logic! If the wildlife didn\'t take it, then where in the Twisting Nether could it have gone?', 66337), -- Tracking the Trail
(88977, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Impossible. My magic has never failed me before... It seems we are at an impasse.\n\nTo be thwarted by something so simple, yet so insidiously effective... is infuriating.', 66337), -- Reenact the Crime
(90907, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope our fair town is treating you well. If you have any concerns at all, bring them to me.', 66337), -- The First to Know
(90875, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tul\'amar smiles sadly at her people.>', 66337), -- Across Worlds
(90874, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tul\'amar holds still, even as you approach.>', 66337), -- Their Violent Ends
(90873, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tul\'amar holds still, even as you approach.>', 66337), -- These Violent Delights
(90872, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Done?', 66337), -- Drenched In It
(90866, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'You. Not die? Good.', 66337), -- Universal Language
(90860, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'The pressure is building... it\'s almost time...\n\nAnd besides, do I even deserve to live? What will they say of me, a member of the Shadowguard, when all is said and done?\n\nDo you think Kifaan could ever forgive me?', 66337), -- Shedding the Yoke
(86997, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'Well? Are the pages in your possession, or will you admit your deception?', 0), -- Spellbook Scuffle
(90858, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Veraan trembles with rage.>\n\nThese kinslayers were willing to sacrifice their own. And in service of what? Xal\'atath\'s will?', 66337), -- Repress the Oppressors
(90852, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Show caution. These rebels are still beings of the Void.', 66337), -- Techno-Magnetic Pulse
(90851, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Degrees of evil is not a question I expected to be pondering.\n\nLet us save who we can and agonize over merits later.', 66337), -- Eating Their Own
(90847, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At the risk of getting my hopes up... do you think Veraan could be among them?\n\nCould I face her now? After the atrocities she\'s committed in the name of the Void?', 66337), -- Truth From Power
(90845, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These keepsakes are some of the last remnants of our home world.\n\nThe memories they contain are powerful. The Shadowguard is right to fear them.', 66337), -- Distant Memories
(90844, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thought the Void coursing through these ethereals was all-consuming.\n\nAnd yet, there seem to be some able to resist its infinite darkness.', 66337), -- Fits of Lucidity
(86973, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I should have expected this attack. Do what you can to protect those who live here.', 66337), -- Halting Harm in Har'mara
(90832, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'Whatever happens next, you\'ve proven you can be trusted.', 66337), -- As Her Voice Goes Silent
(90831, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I see you, $n.', 66337), -- Doing Is Becoming
(90827, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Be careful handling that poison. These creatures are some of the deadliest in all of Harandar.', 66337), -- Only the Poisonous Parts
(90826, 273, 273, 0, 0, 'I appreciate your help, $n.', 66337), -- The Healing Waters of Ahl'ua
(90822, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Something seems to have happened in Murder Row since we left. A crowd is forming.\n\nProceed with caution. I\'m with you.', 66337), -- Murder Row: One Fel Swoop
(90821, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zaen is the mastermind here, or at least he seems to be. We\'ll need to deal with him to truly end this scheme.\n\nTaking out their fel supply line at the harbor will stop the situation from getting any worse while we find him.', 0), -- Murder Row: Harbored Secrets
(90819, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The denizens of Murder Row are tight-lipped, but any information we manage to uncover will be invaluable.', 0), -- Murder Row: Acting the Part
(86956, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must stop the spread of the Lightbloom! Determining its spread will help us fight it in the long run.', 66337), -- The Traveling Flowers
(94677, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'The Rootwarden should be here. We must find out what would be so pressing that would take him away from his responsibilities.', 66337), -- The Missing Rootwarden
(92738, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'The young are often resilient.', 66337), -- Potatoad Tots
(86944, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us hope Eonka is unchanged.', 66337), -- Seeds of the Rift
(92737, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'We must protect Harandar\'s natural species from this invasive growth.', 66337), -- Light Carnage
(86942, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I raised Koozat since he was small enough to fit in my hands. The Lightbloom does not discriminate who it infects.', 66337), -- Culling the Spread
(92728, 0, 603, 0, 0, 'Have you gotten those rowdy little sparks under control?', 66337), -- Dogged Disturbances
(86914, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is the natural state of the fungarians and the rutaani to spread themselves out. At times, this can lead to overgrowth and the crowding out of other species.\n\nMaintaining that balance is important, and is the duty the haranir fulfill as stewards of Harandar.', 66337), -- Tending to Har'mara
(86912, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have survived the Gulf of Memories. Welcome to Har\'mara, friend.', 0), -- Down the Rootways
(86911, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our people have been here for tens of thousands of years, but it was not always so. Once, we lived on the surface as you do.', 0), -- Echoes and Memories
(86910, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Koozat is not usually a violent creature.', 66337), -- Koozat's Trample
(90772, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'If I cannot commune with Jan\'alai, de path of de hash\'ey stops at dis temple.', 66337), -- The Flames Rise Higher
(92697, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you put paint to stone and watched your creativity flow?', 66337), -- Hues of Tomorrow
(86903, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'This really is quite the place, isn\'t it, $p?', 66337), -- The Arcantina
(92696, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Have you collected the ingredients I need?', 66337), -- Colors Born Anew
(86902, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you get those relics out to everyone, $p?', 66337), -- Relinquishing Relics
(92695, 0, 1, 0, 0, 'I fear I ruined everything.\n\nHave you been able to undo the destruction I brought upon this vision?', 66337); -- The Stroke of Storms
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_conditional` (`QuestId`, `PlayerConditionId`, `QuestgiverCreatureId`, `locale`, `Text`, `OrderIndex`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(91627, 47452, 0, 'enUS', 'Ah, $n! It has been far too long. Welcome back to my Haven--a sanctuary from the world\'s turmoil since the days of Anasterian.\n\nSome presume this to be merely a frivolous party, but on these beautiful gilded grounds, decisions have been made over wine that have shaped the fates of entire generations.', 0, 66263), -- Saltheril's Haven
(90875, 139629, 241620, 'enUS', 'You made this possible, $n: my people, safe. They must return, but I must be the one to ensure it.\n\nI cannot walk through that portal with them. I must destroy it to ensure that no domanaar can follow them through and darken our skies as before. \n\nYou have proven yourself to be my ally, but I cannot trust you with this. I can\'t rest until I know they\'re safe.\n\n<She then holds her staff forward, offering it to Juras. Though he seems reluctant to take it, Tul\'amar does not waver.>', 1, 66263), -- Across Worlds
(90875, 67878, 241620, 'enUS', 'You made this possible, $n. We kin, lost and now reunited... but they must return, and I must be the one to ensure it.\n\nI cannot walk through that portal with them. I must destroy it to ensure that no domanaar can follow them through and darken our skies as before. \n\nYou are my kin, but I cannot trust you with this. I can\'t rest until I know they\'re safe.\n\n<She then holds her staff forward, offering it to Juras. Though he seems reluctant to take it, Tul\'amar does not waver.>', 0, 66263), -- Across Worlds
(91606, 20069, 256901, 'enUS', 'Charonus. Weak. Fickle. One of the first domanaar to bow to Xal\'atath. \n\nUnsurprising. Still, let\'s hear if his offer is of any interest. Premature murder is so boring.', 0, 66263), -- Voidscar Arena: Clearing House
(90874, 139629, 241620, 'enUS', 'They want violence? You give them violence. I savored the sight of it.\n\nThose runes look potent. That many should be enough.', 1, 66263), -- Their Violent Ends
(90874, 67878, 241620, 'enUS', 'They want violence? You give them violence. I savored the sight of it.\n\nThose runes look potent. That many should be enough.', 0, 66263), -- Their Violent Ends
(90873, 139629, 241620, 'enUS', '<Tul\'amar nods to the freed draenei hiding behind her.>\n\nWhen we fight, it\'s on our terms.', 1, 66263), -- These Violent Delights
(90873, 67878, 241620, 'enUS', '<Tul\'amar nods to the freed draenei hiding behind her.>\n\nWhen we fight, it\'s on our terms.', 0, 66263), -- These Violent Delights
(90872, 139629, 241620, 'enUS', 'This hellish place... I was kept here for weeks before I slipped my restraints. There are far more of my kin here than when last I chanced a visit.\n\nNow, we save them. And kill these monsters.', 1, 66263), -- Drenched In It
(90872, 67878, 241620, 'enUS', 'This hellish place... I was kept here for weeks before I slipped my restraints. There are far more of our kin here than when last I chanced a visit.\n\nNow, we save our brothers and sisters. And kill these monsters.', 0, 66263), -- Drenched In It
(90866, 139629, 0, 'enUS', 'I\'d have put my people to the task, had the fighting pits not broken so many in body and spirit. \n\nLet us see if my theory is correct.', 1, 66263), -- Universal Language
(90866, 67878, 241620, 'enUS', 'I\'d have put our people to the task, had the fighting pits not broken so many in body and spirit. \n\nLet us see if my theory is correct.', 0, 66263), -- Universal Language
(90782, 139629, 241620, 'enUS', 'Your arrival fills me with cautious hope, alien. I owe you for rescuing my younger brother.\n\nBut I have more to ask of you.', 1, 66263), -- The Nethersent
(90782, 122541, 241620, 'enUS', 'I am filled with cautious hope to see kin of ours in this hellish place, and I owe you for rescuing my younger brother.\n\nBut I have more to ask of you.', 0, 66263), -- The Nethersent
(91382, 143164, 246727, 'enUS', 'Fidoficus will grow so terribly large, that it is he who will be walking you. \n\nOnly then will he be worthy of joining me as my attack behemoth.', 0, 66263), -- Mighty and Superior
(92496, 146074, 0, 'enUS', 'You\'ve done a great honor for our tribe by defendin\' our lands against de Twilight\'s Blade.\n\nBut Idago is not happy that I came back.', 0, 66263), -- Spears Against de Shadow
(92493, 148087, 251669, 'enUS', 'Idago was taken into de crypt! They are sayin\' de big boss Mish\'mosh has somethin\' nasty in store for him.', 0, 66263), -- What Remains of Idago
(89231, 143611, 240975, 'enUS', 'A lovely headdress! From Zak\'kash? Oh...\n\n<Namaji looks troubled.>\n\nBoth Zak\'kash and Kagara want me to go wit\' dem to de festival. What should I do?', 0, 66263), -- A Fighter Not a Lover
(89230, 143611, 240975, 'enUS', 'Dis is from Kagara? I\'ve always wanted one of these! Oh...\n\n<Namaji looks troubled.>\n\nBoth Kagara and Zak\'kash want me to go wit\' dem to de festival. What should I do?', 0, 66263), -- A Lover Not a Fighter
(90822, 139932, 0, 'enUS', 'With no one left to run it, this fel trading operation should be done with... for now, at least.\n\nI will admit, I was not certain of your intentions--but you have earned my respect, $n.', 1, 66192), -- Murder Row: One Fel Swoop
(90822, 42788, 0, 'enUS', 'With no one left to run it, this fel trading operation should be done with... for now, at least.\n\nIt was an honor seeing you work, $ct $n.', 0, 66192), -- Murder Row: One Fel Swoop
(89204, 42230, 0, 'enUS', 'Nice and clean. I\'ve been stealing to make ends meet since I was a kid, but I don\'t get a partner in crime very often.\n\nMaybe I can return the favor one day. You look like you\'ve got some good tricks.', 0, 66192), -- Five Finger Discount
(90669, 39987, 0, 'enUS', 'Ah, so the ruffian managed to find a warlock. A pleasure to make your acquaintance.\n\nYou do certainly look capable. Let us speak, shall we?', 1, 66192), -- Gold is Gold
(90669, 145390, 0, 'enUS', 'Ah, I see the ruffian sent one of her... fellows.\n\nYou do look capable, I suppose. Let us speak, shall we?', 0, 66192), -- Gold is Gold
(90818, 140111, 0, 'enUS', '<Belath\'s expression sours more than usual.>\n\nFear drives people to desperate measures, but fel magic is not a weapon to be wielded lightly.\n\nThe power comes at a cost they do not understand--nor are they trained to withstand those dangers. Not like you and I.', 0, 66192), -- Murder Row: Loose Lips
(90835, 95784, 0, 'enUS', '$ct, your arrival is timely.\n\nI will be brief: I believe there is a widespread resurgence of fel magic use happening in Silvermoon, and it must be stopped.', 0, 66192), -- Murder Row: Rumors Abound
(86559, 54203, 0, 'enUS', 'The rest of your fellow void elves have been dispersed to set up camps or scout.\n\nI am... conflicted over Alleria\'s presence. Much like you, her skills and experience are unspeakably valuable, and yet...\n\nEven moreso than you, the Void in her is so strong... I worry. Keep an eye on her.\n\nThe Void can NEVER be trusted.', 0, 66192), -- The Far, Far Frontier
(86557, 54203, 0, 'enUS', 'Vile beasts. Did you sense it?\n\nThey all reek of Void.\n\n<Lothraxion curls his lip.> \n\nLike you.', 0, 66192), -- A Matter of Strife and Death
(86558, 54203, 0, 'enUS', 'You void elves risk corruption, and yet are most suited to understanding the world around us. We need your expertise, but cannot trust you.\n\nIt irks me, but I have already sent for more scouts.', 0, 66192), -- Save a Piece of Mind
(86549, 54203, 0, 'enUS', 'This... this power! I have never felt the Void like this. \n\nIt is all-consuming. Like when we were overwhelmed in Telogrus... \n\nBut you overcame it. We can all overcome it. We are ren\'dorei.', 0, 66192), -- No Fear of the Dark
(86841, 135389, 237594, 'enUS', 'I trust you found what you needed, Highlord $p?', 0, 66192), -- Relics of Paladins Past
(86839, 135389, 0, 'enUS', 'Highlord $p!\n\nNearly all the paladins here were summoned to the Sunwell to fight the Void, so we could definitely use your help.', 0, 66192), -- Relics of Light's Hope
(90622, 144999, 243226, 'enUS', 'Wow, shocked! Fungal Fellowship beat Glow Guard!\n\nI knew $p strong. But did not know if training could be enough.\n\nNot one fungarian was bet on Fungal Fellowship. We did not think Glow Guard could be defeat. \n\nNow every fungarian know $p is best teacher of strong!', 3, 66263), -- Not-Yet Defeated Champions
(90622, 144998, 243226, 'enUS', 'Wow, shocked! Puffguard beat Glow Guard!\n\nI knew $p strong. But did not know if training could be enough.\n\nNot one fungarian was bet on Puffguard. We did not think Glow Guard could be defeat. \n\nNow every fungarian know $p is best teacher of strong!', 2, 66263), -- Not-Yet Defeated Champions
(90622, 144997, 243226, 'enUS', 'Wow, shocked! Sporesworn beat Glow Guard!\n\nI knew $p strong. But did not know if training could be enough.\n\nNot one fungarian was bet on Sporesworn. We did not think Glow Guard could be defeat. \n\nNow every fungarian know $p is best teacher of strong!', 1, 66263), -- Not-Yet Defeated Champions
(90622, 144996, 243226, 'enUS', 'Wow, shocked! Ringcaps beat Glow Guard!\n\nI knew $p strong. But did not know if training could be enough.\n\nNot one fungarian was bet on Ringcaps. We did not think Glow Guard could be defeat. \n\nNow every fungarian know $p is best teacher of strong!', 0, 66263), -- Not-Yet Defeated Champions
(90621, 144999, 243226, 'enUS', 'Done teaching, now? Let\'s see what Fungal Fellowship can do.', 3, 66263), -- Tiny Heroes' Journeys
(90621, 144998, 243226, 'enUS', 'Done teaching, now? Let\'s see what Puffguard can do.', 2, 66263), -- Tiny Heroes' Journeys
(90621, 144997, 243226, 'enUS', 'Done teaching, now? Let\'s see what Sporesworn can do.', 1, 66263), -- Tiny Heroes' Journeys
(90621, 144996, 243226, 'enUS', 'Done teaching, now? Let\'s see what Ringcaps can do.', 0, 66263), -- Tiny Heroes' Journeys
(92617, 144999, 251723, 'enUS', '$p did not die! Ziny healed $p.\n\nWould have been Ziny\'s fault if $p died, but $p lived. Because Ziny healed, even though enemies were scary.\n\nSo scary.\n\nHooray! $p welcome. For help.\n\nAnd $p is thanked. For showing can do together.\n\nCan be the Fungal Fellowship now. Will win Grudge Pit, for sure.', 3, 66263), -- Mushrooming Resilience
(92617, 144998, 251723, 'enUS', '$p did not die! Ziny healed $p.\n\nWould have been Ziny\'s fault if $p died, but $p lived. Because Ziny healed, even though enemies were scary.\n\nSo scary.\n\nHooray! $p welcome. For help.\n\nAnd $p is thanked. For showing can do together.\n\nCan be the Puffguard now. Will win Grudge Pit, for sure.', 2, 66263), -- Mushrooming Resilience
(92617, 144997, 251723, 'enUS', '$p did not die! Ziny healed $p.\n\nWould have been Ziny\'s fault if $p died, but $p lived. Because Ziny healed, even though enemies were scary.\n\nSo scary.\n\nHooray! $p welcome. For help.\n\nAnd $p is thanked. For showing can do together.\n\nCan be the Sporesworn now. Will win Grudge Pit, for sure.', 1, 66263), -- Mushrooming Resilience
(92617, 144996, 251723, 'enUS', '$p did not die! Ziny healed $p.\n\nWould have been Ziny\'s fault if $p died, but $p lived. Because Ziny healed, even though enemies were scary.\n\nSo scary.\n\nHooray! $p welcome. For help.\n\nAnd $p is thanked. For showing can do together.\n\nCan be the Ringcaps now. Will win Grudge Pit, for sure.', 0, 66263), -- Mushrooming Resilience
(92616, 144999, 251722, 'enUS', 'Sporegliders very scary. Could still sneak up and attack. Hurt Brakko\'s cap.\n\nBut $p made Brakko practice. Now can fight sporegliders, even when scared.\n\nScared does not mean Brakko have to run.\n\nReady now to fight for the Fungal Fellosh.\n\nEven if we fight sporegliders, Brakko will not run.', 3, 66263), -- Mushrooming Courage
(92616, 144998, 251722, 'enUS', 'Sporegliders very scary. Could still sneak up and attack. Hurt Brakko\'s cap.\n\nBut $p made Brakko practice. Now can fight sporegliders, even when scared.\n\nScared does not mean Brakko have to run.\n\nReady now to fight for the Puffguard.\n\nEven if we fight sporegliders, Brakko will not run.', 2, 66263), -- Mushrooming Courage
(92616, 144997, 251722, 'enUS', 'Sporegliders very scary. Could still sneak up and attack. Hurt Brakko\'s cap.\n\nBut $p made Brakko practice. Now can fight sporegliders, even when scared.\n\nScared does not mean Brakko have to run.\n\nReady now to fight for the Sporesworn.\n\nEven if we fight sporegliders, Brakko will not run.', 1, 66263), -- Mushrooming Courage
(92616, 144996, 251722, 'enUS', 'Sporegliders very scary. Could still sneak up and attack. Hurt Brakko\'s cap.\n\nBut $p made Brakko practice. Now can fight sporegliders, even when scared.\n\nScared does not mean Brakko have to run.\n\nReady now to fight for the Ringcaps.\n\nEven if we fight sporegliders, Brakko will not run.', 0, 66263), -- Mushrooming Courage
(92618, 144999, 247252, 'enUS', 'Tuktuk could lose! Be beaten.\n\nVery scary. But $p would still be friend. Brakko would still be friend. Ziny would still be friend. \n\nWould still be the Fungus Falls. Will meet back at Grudge Pit.\n\nOk, Tuktuk will try best.\n\nWill shoot poison again.\n\nSo much poison.\n\nEverywhere.', 3, 66263), -- Mushrooming Confidence
(92618, 144998, 247252, 'enUS', 'Tuktuk could lose! Be beaten.\n\nVery scary. But $p would still be friend. Brakko would still be friend. Ziny would still be friend. \n\nWould still be the Puffguard. Very good name.\n\nOk, Tuktuk will try best. Will meet back at Grudge Pit.\n\nWill shoot poison again.\n\nSo much poison.\n\nEverywhere.', 2, 66263), -- Mushrooming Confidence
(92618, 144997, 247252, 'enUS', 'Tuktuk could lose! Be beaten.\n\nVery scary. But $p would still be friend. Brakko would still be friend. Ziny would still be friend. \n\nWould still be the Sporesworn.\n\nOk, Tuktuk will try best. Will meet back at Grudge Pit.\n\nWill shoot poison again.\n\nSo much poison.\n\nEverywhere.', 1, 66263), -- Mushrooming Confidence
(92618, 144996, 247252, 'enUS', 'Tuktuk could lose! Be beaten.\n\nVery scary. But $p would still be friend. Brakko would still be friend. Ziny would still be friend. \n\nWould still be the Ringcaps.\n\nOk, Tuktuk will try best. Will meet back at Grudge Pit.\n\nWill shoot poison again.\n\nSo much poison.\n\nEverywhere.', 0, 66263), -- Mushrooming Confidence
(90620, 144999, 247245, 'enUS', 'Was sure Brakko was strong enough. Was train with strong $p!\n\nBut Brakko is scared of sporegliders. Will eat cap!\n\nBrakko so sad to fail $p.\n\nZiny and Tuktuk too. All run out.\n\nWe run out, and Fungal Fellosh were lose.\n\nBut how can not run out, when sporegliders attack?', 3, 66263), -- To the Ring
(90620, 144998, 247245, 'enUS', 'Was sure Brakko was strong enough. Was train with strong $p!\n\nBut Brakko is scared of sporegliders. Will eat cap!\n\nBrakko so sad to fail $p.\n\nZiny and Tuktuk too. All run out.\n\nWe run out, and Puffguard were lose.\n\nBut how can not run out, when sporegliders attack?', 2, 66263), -- To the Ring
(90620, 144997, 247245, 'enUS', 'Was sure Brakko was strong enough. Was train with strong $p!\n\nBut Brakko is scared of sporegliders. Will eat cap!\n\nBrakko so sad to fail $p.\n\nZiny and Tuktuk too. All run out.\n\nWe run out, and Sporesworn were lose.\n\nBut how can not run out, when sporegliders attack?', 1, 66263), -- To the Ring
(90620, 144996, 247245, 'enUS', 'Was sure Brakko was strong enough. Was train with strong $p!\n\nBut Brakko is scared of sporegliders. Will eat cap!\n\nBrakko so sad to fail $p.\n\nZiny and Tuktuk too. All run out.\n\nWe run out, and Ringcaps were lose.\n\nBut how can not run out, when sporegliders attack?', 0, 66263), -- To the Ring
(91270, 144999, 251715, 'enUS', 'Fungal Fell...owship, ok. Now we ready.\n\nWill run into pit together, shout the Fungal Fello...sip, eh...\n\nCrowd will cheer, then will be new champions!', 3, 66263), -- The Most Important Thing
(91270, 144998, 251715, 'enUS', 'Puffguard, perfect! Was best name.\n\nNow we ready.\n\nWill run into pit together, shout the Puffguard, eh...\n\nCrowd will cheer, then will be new champions!', 2, 66263), -- The Most Important Thing
(91270, 144997, 251715, 'enUS', 'Sporesworn, perfect! Now we ready.\n\nWill run into pit together, shout the Sporesworn, eh...\n\nCrowd will cheer, then will be new champions!', 1, 66263), -- The Most Important Thing
(91270, 144996, 251715, 'enUS', 'Ringcaps, perfect! Now we ready.\n\nWill run into pit together, shout the Ringcaps, eh...\n\nCrowd will cheer, then will be new champions!', 0, 66263); -- The Most Important Thing
INSERT INTO `quest_request_items_conditional` (`QuestId`, `PlayerConditionId`, `QuestgiverCreatureId`, `locale`, `Text`, `OrderIndex`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(88708, 137552, 236930, 'enUS', 'We\'re too late, $n. Matrean\'s mind is lost... and we are now duty-bound. \n\nI\'ve known this day might come... the day my partner falls prey to the Void\'s corrution.\n\nPlease... can you do this for me? Find and slay the nightmare that Matrean has become.', 0, 66263), -- Violent Conclusions
(90872, 139629, 241620, 'enUS', 'They\'re all drenched in violence? Good. I apologize on behalf of anyone who seemed ungrateful.', 1, 66263), -- Drenched In It
(90872, 67878, 241620, 'enUS', 'They\'re all drenched in violence? Good. I apologize on behalf of anyone who seemed ungrateful.', 0, 66263), -- Drenched In It
(90866, 139629, 241620, 'enUS', 'If you\'re spotted by the domanaar, don\'t let them follow you here.', 1, 66263), -- Universal Language
(90866, 67878, 241620, 'enUS', 'If you\'re spotted by the domanaar, don\'t let them follow you here.', 0, 66263), -- Universal Language
(92497, 146074, 251522, 'enUS', 'Appreciate ya, $n. For freeing me and for keeping an eye on dis one here.', 0, 66263), -- Simply Magical
(92493, 148087, 0, 'enUS', 'Revantusk Sedge is swarmin\' with these foul mages. You\'re doin\' de loa\'s work.', 0, 66263), -- What Remains of Idago
(87254, 141320, 0, 'enUS', 'De liver ritual did nothin\'?', 0, 66263), -- Curse Cleanse
